%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22India-Funded%20Hydro%20Projects%20in%20Bhutan%20Under%20Scanner%20After%20Sikkim%20Teesta%20Disaster%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15183235%2F353044344_581035810846417_3957435971921388168_n.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20the%20Sikkim%20Teesta%20disaster%20that%20resulted%20in%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%201%2C200%20MW%20Teesta-III%20dam%20and%20left%20nearly%20100%20people%20dead%2C%20two%20of%20the%20three%20India-funded%20mega%20hydro%20projects%20currently%20being%20constructed%20in%20Bhutan%20have%20now%20come%20under%20the%20scanner%20and%20changes%20are%20being%20made%20in%20their%20design%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fthe-shadow-from-the-fallen-sikkim-dam-falls-on-indias-hydroelectric-projects-in-bhutan%2Farticle67420574.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Sunday%2C%20October%2015.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20projects%20are%20the%201%2C200%20MW%20Punatsangchhu%20Stage-I%20(Puna-I)%20and%20the%201%2C020%20MW%20Punatsangchhu%20Stage-II%20(Puna-II)%2C%20on%20the%20Punatsangchhu%20River%2C%20less%20than%20100%20km%20from%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20capital%2C%20Thimphu.%20Per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fthe-shadow-from-the-fallen-sikkim-dam-falls-on-indias-hydroelectric-projects-in-bhutan%2Farticle67420574.ece%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20projects%2C%20along%20with%20the%20660%20MW%20Kholongchu%20project%2C%20are%20estimated%20to%20cost%20%E2%82%B921%2C637.28%20crore%2C%20and%20are%20being%20funded%20by%20India%20and%20will%20benefit%20northern%20and%20eastern%20Indian%20states.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20the%20Central%20Electricity%20Authority%20(CEA)%20uploaded%20a%20note%20in%20February%20this%20year%20(and%20updated%20in%20August)%20on%20the%20projects%20completed%2C%20being%20constructed%2C%20and%20pursued%20under%20a%202006%20agreement%20on%20cooperation%20in%20the%20field%20of%20hydroelectric%20power%20signed%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPer%20the%20CEA%20note%2C%20the%20Puna-I%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20commissioned%20in%202024-25%2C%20but%20that%20the%20commissioning%20is%20being%20delayed%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20to%20movement%2Fsubsidence%20of%20right%20bank%20hill%20mass%20in%20the%20dam%20area%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20added%20that%3A%20%E2%80%9CTreatment%2Fstabilisation%20of%20the%20right%20bank%20and%20completion%20of%20dam%20work%20under%20progress.%20The%20option%20of%20providing%20a%20barrage%20in%20the%20upstream%20and%20abandoning%20of%20the%20dam%20is%20being%20studied.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPer%20the%20note%2C%20the%20Puna-II%20is%20targeted%20for%20commissioning%20in%202023-24.%20The%20Hindu%20reported%20that%20as%20per%20the%20note%2C%20%E2%80%9Cremedial%20measures%20are%20under%20progress%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Cpoor%20geological%20strata%20and%20shear%20zone%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20left%20bank%20and%20foundation%20of%20the%20dam%20and%20its%20head%20race%20tunnel%20(which%20connects%20the%20water%20intake%20at%20a%20dam%20site%20to%20the%20powerhouse%20for%20hydropower%20generation).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEnvironmental%20activist%20and%20water%20and%20dam%20safety%20expert%20Himanshu%20Thakkar%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20likely%20change%20in%20design%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9Cadmission%20of%20a%20major%20failure%20by%20these%20agencies%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInternational%20landslide%20experts%20like%20Dave%20Petley%20have%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20blunder%20to%20start%20a%20dam%20at%20the%20location%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20on%20the%20debris%20of%20past%20landslides%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20also%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%20quoted%20anonymous%20Indian%20government%20officials%20as%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cno%20final%20decision%20has%20been%20taken%20on%20the%20Bhutan%20projects%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20experts%20were%20studying%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctechnical%20aspects%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20projects%20including%20geology.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20Prime%20Minister%20Lotay%20Tshering%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20he%20was%20confident%20that%20the%20problems%20would%20be%20resolved.%20Bhutanese%20technical%20experts%20have%20said%20that%20if%20the%20dam%20is%20not%20feasible%2C%20then%20probably%20a%20smaller%20dam%20or%20barrage%20is%20required.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Indian%20government%20experts%20have%20said%20that%20the%20dam%20is%20%E2%80%9Cfeasible%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20PM%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20one%20estimate%2C%20about%2075%25%20of%20all%20electricity%20generated%20in%20Bhutan%20is%20exported%20to%20India%20and%20the%20revenue%20from%20the%20exports%20constitutes%2025%25%20of%20its%20gross%20domestic%20product.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELocal%20communities%20living%20in%20areas%20near%20dams%20in%20Bhutan%20have%20reported%20similar%20issues%20as%20seen%20in%20houses%20near%20dams%20in%20the%20Indian%20Himalaya%3A%20cracks%20on%20their%20houses%2C%20which%20first%20occurred%20right%20after%20the%20project%20work%20for%20a%20dam%20began.%20For%20instance%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThird%20Pole%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fenergy%2Fin-photos-hydropower-leaves-cracked-houses-across-bhutan%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202020%20that%20houses%20near%20the%20Mangdechhu%20Dam%20on%20the%20Mangdechhu%20River%20in%20Bhutan%20%E2%80%93%20commissioned%20and%20funded%20by%20India.%20Per%20one%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.power-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fmangdechhu-hydroelectric-project-trongsa-dzongkhag%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20is%20one%20of%20the%2013%20hydro%20projects%20developed%20as%20part%20of%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20initiative%20to%20generate%2010GW%20of%20hydropower%20with%20support%20from%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697375061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15183235%2F353044344_581035810846417_3957435971921388168_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-funded-hydro-projects-bhutan-scanner%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Environmental%20activist%20and%20water%20and%20dam%20safety%20expert%20Himanshu%20Thakkar%20told%20The%20Hindu%20that%20the%20likely%20change%20in%20design%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9Cadmission%20of%20a%20major%20failure%20by%20these%20agencies%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-funded-hydro-projects-bhutan-scanner%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Eritrean%20asylum%20seekers%20in%20Israel%3A%20'Our%20second%20country%20is%20bleeding'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697375027000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1CCD%2Fproduction%2F_131437370_gettyimages-1725782490.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67115875%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eritrean%20asylum%20seekers%20in%20Isra