nce-for-north-korea-to-upgrade-air-force-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Default%20risks%20loom%20for%20nearly%20%242%20trillion%20of%20junk-rated%20debt%20as%20US%20companies%20hit%20with%20higher%20interest%20rates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224653%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Moody's%20logo%20on%20the%20side%20of%20a%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65282f4355f52b01b35e28fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222326%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMoody's%20logo%3Cp%3EEMMANUEL%20DUNAND%20%2F%20Staff%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EDefault%20and%20refinancing%20risks%20are%20climbing%20for%20US%20companies%20over%20the%20next%20several%20years%2C%20Moody's%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EJunk-rated%20firms%20have%20%241.87%20trillion%20in%20debt%20maturing%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EStrategists%20said%20speculative-grade%20credit%20faces%20more%20pain%20amid%20higher%20rates%20and%20tighter%20financial%20conditions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENon-investment%20grade%20US%20companies%20face%20growing%20refinancing%20and%20default%20risks%20with%20interest%20rates%20expected%20to%20stay%20high%20and%20financial%20conditions%20for%20borrowers%20tightening%2C%20according%20to%20Moody's%20Investors%20Service%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ratings%20agency%20says%20about%20%241.87%20trillion%20of%20junk-rated%20debt%20is%20maturing%20between%202024%20and%202028.%C2%A0That%20signifies%20a%2027%25%20jump%20from%20the%20%241.47%20trillion%20recorded%20in%20last%20year's%20study%20for%202023-2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDebt%20maturing%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years%20accounts%20for%20about%2018%25%20of%20the%20five-year%20total%2C%20Moody's%20said%2C%20though%20the%20absolute%20amount%20for%20those%20two%20years%20has%20surged%2025%25%20compared%20to%20last%20year's%20study%2C%20to%20hit%20%24333%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoody's%20analysts%20expect%20the%20US%20speculative-grade%20default%20rate%20to%20peak%20at%205.6%25%20in%20January%202024%2C%20before%20easing%20to%204.6%25%20by%20August%202024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221887%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Moody's%20Investor%20Service%20debt%20refinance%20risk%202028%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65280b196561dd877e78f771%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221176%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERefinancing%20risks%20are%20climbing%20for%20US%20companies.%3Cp%3EMoody's%20Investor%20Service%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increase%20%E2%80%94%20reflecting%20higher%20maturities%20for%20revolving%20credit%20facilities%2C%20loans%20and%20bonds%20%E2%80%94%20comes%20amid%20weak%20macroeconomic%20and%20credit%20conditions%2C%20raising%20companies'%20refinancing%20and%20default%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20Moody's%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20heightened%20risks%20stem%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20historic%20interest%20rate%20hiking%20campaign%20and%20the%20end%20of%20the%20easy-money%20era.%20A%20higher-for-longer%20rate%20environment%20puts%20pressure%20on%20businesses%20because%20borrowing%20becomes%20more%20expensive%20and%20investors%20will%20demand%20a%20higher%20yield%20for%20holding%20riskier%20corporate%20debt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20with%20ratings%20of%20B2%20or%20below%20have%20to%20pay%20off%20%24206%20billion%20in%20debt%20coming%20due%20in%202024%20and%202025%2C%20which%20will%20then%20balloon%20to%20roughly%20%241.1%20trillion%20from%202024%20to%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoody's%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20issuance%20of%20credit%20remains%20low%2C%20with%20US%20marketed%20bank%20credit%20facilities%20for%20January%20to%20September%202023%20down%2024%25%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20period%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYear-to-date%20bond%20issuance%20is%20up%2026%25%20but%20remains%20below%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20reflecting%20investors'%20reluctance%20to%20lock%20in%20fixed-%20coupon%20income%20while%20interest%20rates%20were%20rising%20and%20companies%20awaiting%20a%20more%20favorable%20market%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20note%20though%20that%20borrowing%20costs%20have%20come%20down%20in%20the%20last%20year%20as%20market%20sentiment%20has%20improved%20and%20recession%20fears%20have%20ebbed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Moody's%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bpull-forward%26quot%3B%20effect%20and%20%26quot%3Bamend-and-extend%26quot%3B%20activity%20heighten%20refinancing%20risk%20for%20some%20corporate%20loans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies'%20tendency%20to%20refinance%20several%20tranches%20of%20debt%20in%20a%20single%20bank%20credit%20agreement%20when%20the%20first%20tranche%2C%20typically%20a%20revolver%2C%20comes%20due%20could%20more%20than%20double%20their%202024-26%20bank%20debt%20maturities%20to%20over%20%241%20trillion%2C%20representing%2080%25%20of%20the%20total%20five-year%20bank%20maturities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20as%20the%20share%20of%20maturities%20of%20lower-rated%20debt%20climbs%2C%20so%20too%20will%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20refinancing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDebt%20from%20distressed%20companies%2C%20or%20those%20rated%20Caa%20and%20lower%20by%20Moody's%2C%20account%20for%2019%25%20of%202024-2025%20maturities.%20That's%20up%20from%20the%2016%25%20due%20in%20the%20first%20two%20years%20of%20last%20year's%20study.%20An%20increasing%20number%20of%20companies%20may%20find%20it%20harder%20to%20refinance%20maturities%20at%20interest%20rates%20they%20can%20afford%2C%20Moody's%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjunk-bonds-default-risk-trillion-corporate-debt-refinance-interest-rates-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C