rafted%20immediately%2C%20but%20this%20could%20change%20if%20mobilization%20laws%20are%20enacted%20to%20widen%20the%20recruitment%20net.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtem%20added%20that%20he's%20also%20disenchanted%20by%20the%20lack%20of%20opportunities%20in%20the%20country's%20war-crippled%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20escape%20plan%20involved%20crossing%20over%20into%20Romania.%20He%20took%20a%20westbound%20train%20to%20a%20town%20near%20the%20border%2C%20but%20when%20he%20got%20off%2C%20he%20and%20the%20other%20men%20on%20board%20were%20confronted%20by%20police%20officers%20about%20why%20they%20were%20traveling%20within%2020%20miles%20of%20the%20frontier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtem%20said%20that%20several%20of%20them%20were%20taken%20to%20a%20police%20station%20and%20questioned%20further%20before%20being%20put%20on%20a%20bus%20that%20took%20them%20back%20deeper%20into%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20men%20caught%20was%20in%20his%2050s%20and%20traveling%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20children.%20Artem%20later%20learnt%20that%20he%20was%20taken%20straight%20to%20a%20military-registration%20and%20enlistment%20office%20to%20join%20the%20army%2C%20Artem%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20father%20and%20son%20live%20together%20in%20the%20family%20home%20Bohdan%20built%20himself.%20His%20wife%20and%20daughter%20are%20refugees%20in%20Belgium.%20%26quot%3BMy%20family%20is%20divided%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohdan%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohdan%20agreed%20that%20prospects%20were%20grim%20for%20his%20only%20son%2C%20even%20if%20he's%20not%20sent%20to%20the%20front.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20not%20much%20work%20or%20quality%20education%20for%20young%20men%20during%20wartime%2C%20so%20some%20of%20them%20want%20to%20leave%2C%20but%20they%20can't%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Artem%20said%20he%20was%20contemplating%20whether%20it's%20worth%20trying%20to%20flee%20Ukraine%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYoung%20men%20at%20a%20checkpoint%20near%20the%20border%20told%20me%20not%20to%20bother%20trying%2C%26quot%3B%20Artem%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20warned%20that%20the%20forests%20ahead%20were%20full%20of%20bears%20and%20snipers.%26quot%3B%20Insider%20could%20not%20verify%20the%20claim%20regarding%20snipers.%20The%20route%20into%20Romania%20often%20involves%20a%20risky%20crossing%20over%20the%20Carpathian%20Mountains%2C%20which%20is%20home%20to%20brown%20bears%20and%20wolves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Artem%20considers%20his%20next%20moves%2C%20he%20awaits%20a%20fine%20for%20his%20attempt%20to%20leave%20Ukraine%20unlawfully%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20an%20imprisonable%20offense.%20He%20hasn't%20received%20a%20letter%20yet%20but%20estimates%20it%20will%20be%20about%201%2C000%20hryvnia%2C%20or%20about%20%2427.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohdan%20told%20Insider%20that%20last%20week%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20his%20managed%20to%20cross%20the%20border%20into%20Hungary.%20He%20paid%20about%20%246%2C400%20to%20get%20instructions%20from%20a%20people%20smuggler%20who%20told%20him%20where%20to%20cut%20through%20barbed%20wire%20with%20pliers%2C%20his%20friend%20told%20him.%20He%20made%20it%20across%20and%20is%20now%20in%20Montenegro.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20chose%20Hungary%20over%20Romania%20or%20Moldova%2C%20his%20friend%20said%2C%20because%20he%20believed%20the%20border%20guards%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20beat%20him%20up%20and%20perceived%20Hungary%20as%20more%20accepting%20of%20Ukrainian%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E80%2C000%20Ukrainian%20men%20have%20crossed%20over%20to%20Poland%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ruslana%20Danylkina%2C%2019%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20who%20lost%20her%20leg%20in%20the%20fighting%20near%20Kherson%2C%20holds%20her%20crutches%20in%20a%20city%20hospital%20in%20Odesa%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20Feb.%2027%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652820bb55f52b01b35e13f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20who%20lost%20her%20leg%20in%20the%20fighting%20near%20Kherson.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FLibkos%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20men%20ages%2018%20to%2060%20have%20been%20barred%20from%20leaving%20the%20country%20since%20martial%20law%20was%20imposed%20at%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20invasion%20on%20February%2024%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Verkhovna%20Rada%2C%20Ukraine's%20parliament%2C%20voted%20again%20in%20July%20to%20extend%20martial%20law%20and%20general%20mobilization%20by%20another%2090%20days%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Feng%2Fnews%2F2023%2F07%2F27%2F7413087%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkrainska%20Pravda%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20It's%20the%20eighth%20extension%20since%20the%20invasion%20began%20and%20is%20in%20place%20until%20November%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F18%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fukraine-russia-war-casualties.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20US%20officials%2C%20who%20spoke%20anonymously%2C%20estimated%2070%2C000%20Ukrainian%20troops%20had%20been%20killed%20and%20100%2C000%20to%20120%2C000%20wounded.%20In%20the%20first%20days%20of%20the%20war%2C%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20volunteered%20to%20fight%2C%20but%20Ukraine%20is%20now%20more%20dependent%20on%20enlistments.%20The%20Armed%20Forces%20of%20Ukraine%20need%20to%20replace%20their%20dwindling%20numbers%2C%20and%20men%20leaving%20the%20country%20despite%20martial%20law%20could%20have%20long-term%20consequences%20for%20military%20mobilizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Poland%20alone%2C%20an%20estimated%2080%2C000%20men%20%E2%80%94%20the%20equivalent%20to%2020%20military%20brigades%20in%20Ukraine's%20army%20%E2%80%94%20ages%2018%20to%2060%20who%20may%20have%20been%20eligible%20for%20military%20service%20entered%20the%20country%20between%20February%2024%2C%202022%2C%20and%20August%2031%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Poland's%20Border%20Guard.%20The%20whereabouts%20of%20the%20men%20are%20not%20known%2C%20the%20Polish%20news%20outlet%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rp.pl%2Fswiat%2Fart39049061-polska-zaczela-wydawac-ukrainie-jej-obywateli-ktorzy-trudnia-sie-przemytem-ludzi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERzeczpospolita%C2%A0reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Polish%20Border%20Guard%2C%20Lt.%20Anna%20Michalska%2C%20said%20it%20was%20not%20known%20how%20many%20met%20the%20exemption%20requirements%2C%20the%20Kyiv%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20authorities%20say%20they%20have%20caught%206%2C100%20men%20attempting%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20at%20border%20crossings%20using%20fraudulent%20or%20unauthorized%20documents.%20Over%2013%2C000%20who%20wanted%20to%20slip%20out%20of%20Ukraine%20have%20been%20caught%2C%20often%2C%20like%20Artem%2C%20collared%20at%20bus%20and%20train%20stations%20before%20they%20reach%20the%20border%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Feurope%2F2023%2F08%2F31%2Fthousands-of-ukrainian-men-are-avoiding-military-service%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Economist%20reported%20in%20September%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrekking%20across%20the%20country%20to%20escape%20via%20remote%20parts%20of%20the%20border%20can%20end%20in%20disaster.%20For%20example%2C%2019%20have%20drowned%20in%20the%20Tisza%20river%2C%20which%20flows%20along%20part%20of%20Ukraine's%20border%20with%20Hungary%20and%20Romania%2C%20The%20Economist%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'White%20tickets'%20to%20freedom%3A%20buying%20medical%20exemptions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227285%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Doctor%20making%20notes%20while%20on%20video%20call%20with%20patient%20-%20stock%20photo.%5C%22%20ch