%20these%2C%20honestly%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20said.%20To%20be%20fair%2C%20I%20don't%20often%20write%20the%20one-liner%2C%20pub-style%20trivia%20questions%20that%20trivia%20enthusiasts%20and%20beer%20lovers%20alike%20play%20every%20Tuesday%20night.%20In%20fact%2C%20most%20of%20the%20people%20who%20compete%20on%20my%20questions%20aren't%20legally%20allowed%20to%20drink.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20journalism%2C%20I%20write%20and%20edit%20trivia%20questions%20for%20various%20high-school%20and%20college%20competitions%20as%20a%20side%20gig.%20I've%20made%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20writing%20and%20editing%20thousands%20of%20questions%20in%20the%20last%20year%2C%20and%20I'm%20still%20going%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20questions%20are%20written%20for%20everyone%20from%20elementary%20schoolers%20to%20graduate%20students%2C%20meaning%20one%20day%20I'm%20writing%2075-word%20questions%20on%20the%20most%20basic%20of%20history%20facts%2C%20and%20another%20I'm%20spending%20half%20an%20hour%20on%20a%20250-word%20question%20about%20obscure%20classical%20music.%20For%20many%20of%20them%2C%20the%20answers%20are%20much%2C%20much%20harder%20than%20what%20you%20would%20ever%20see%20on%20Jeopardy!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELearning%20more%20about%20the%20world%20through%20writing%20questions%20helps%20me%20pay%20my%20bills%2C%20do%20my%20job%20as%20an%20economy%20reporter%20better%2C%20and%20ultimately%20connect%20with%20people%20from%20all%20sorts%20of%20backgrounds%20%E2%80%94%20a%20particularly%20useful%20perk%20as%20a%20recent%20graduate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loneliness-spends-money-to-make-friends-2023-9%5C%22%3Etrying%20to%20make%20new%20friends%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20they've%20helped%20many%20in%20the%20quiz%20bowl%20community%20want%20to%20learn%20more%20and%20become%20more%20inquisitive%20about%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20art%20of%20the%20trivia%20question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20these%20gigs%20was%20years%20in%20the%20making.%20I%20started%20playing%20for%20my%20high-school%20quiz%20bowl%20team%20as%20a%20freshman%2C%20learning%20the%20ins%20and%20outs%20of%20which%20artists%20were%20asked%20about%2C%20what%20authors%20were%20worth%20studying%2C%20and%20what%20historical%20events%20were%20fair%20game.%20I%20started%20as%20a%2014-year-old%20not%20knowing%20the%20order%20of%20the%20US%20presidents%2C%20and%20by%20the%20following%20year%2C%20I%20was%20answering%20questions%20about%20each%20president's%20specific%20policies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20attending%20national%20competitions%20in%20high%20school%2C%20I%20joined%20the%20Columbia%20University%20quiz%20bowl%20team%2C%20winning%20a%20national%20competition%20in%202021.%20While%20in%20college%2C%20though%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20enjoyed%20writing%20and%20editing%20questions%20even%20more%20than%20competing%2C%20and%20I%20successfully%20applied%20to%20a%20few%20companies%20looking%20for%20writers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20weeks%2C%20I%20was%20writing%20as%20many%20as%20100%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcoloradoqb.org%2Finfo%2Fpyramidal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epyramidal%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20questions%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20the%20more%20obscure%20information%20comes%20first%2C%20followed%20by%20increasingly%20more%20well-known%20clues%20%E2%80%94%20on%20everything%20from%20Asian%20geography%20to%20British%20poets%20to%20jazz%20standards.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20I%20graduated%20college%20that%20I%20saw%20more%20opportunities%20open%20up%20through%20word%20of%20mouth%20and%20online%20applications%2C%20especially%20now%20that%20I%20could%20write%20collegiate%20questions%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20notoriously%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20practice%20and%20lots%20of%20reading%20%E2%80%94%20at%20one%20point%2C%20a%20book%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20I%20kept%20improving.%20Sometimes%C2%A0my%20questions%20fell%20flat%20or%20were%20written%20in%20the%20wrong%20order%2C%20though%20I%20became%20more%20confident%20in%20my%20craft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20use%20%26quot%3Bcraft%26quot%3B%20intentionally.%20Players%20only%20want%20to%20hear%20the%20same%20Jane%20Austen%20or%20Frederick%20the%20Great%20clues%20so%20many%20times.%20Part%20of%20what%20makes%20quiz%20bowl%20writing%20so%20fun%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20keeps%20me%20going%20even%20when%20it%20feels%20like%20I've%20asked%20about%20everything%20I%20could%20think%20of%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20figuring%20out%20a%20fresh%20and%20interesting%20%3Cem%3Eway%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20ask%20about%20a%20topic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20joy%20I%20get%20when%20a%20player%20shouts%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20cool%20clue%26quot%3B%20for%20one%20of%20my%20questions%20is%20often%20unmatched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUsing%20trivia%20to%20inform%20my%20reporting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20as%20I%20learn%20new%20facts%20through%20writing%20questions%2C%20I%20notice%20that%20hidden%20within%20them%20are%20stories.%20For%20example%2C%20after%20researching%20historical%20questions%20on%20the%20Hmong%20people%20over%20the%20last%20year%20or%20two%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20many%20new%20Hmong%20businesses%20have%20been%20opening%20across%20the%20country%20this%20year%2C%20inspiring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhmong-cuisine-culture-philosophy-business-food-industry-renaissance-farming-agriculture-2023-6%5C%22%3Ean%20enterprise%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20completed%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20knowledge%20of%20the%20history%20of%20the%20nation's%20Chinatowns%20and%20Chinese%20American%20culture%20from%20writing%20questions%20inspired%20a%20lengthy%20story%20on%20how%20luxury%20development%20has%20in%20many%20ways%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F05%2F14%2Fchinatown-rapid-luxury-development.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eharmed%20the%20fabrics%20of%20Chinese%20encla