india.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisrael-army-readies-for-gaza-invasion-as-civilians-flee%2Famp_articleshow%2F104442411.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22It%E2%80%99s%20official%3A%20The%20era%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20global%20dominance%20is%20over%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Xi%20Jinping%20portrait%20cracking%20with%20yellow%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529b88855f52b01b35fa95d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChina%20has%20reached%20the%20end%20of%20its%20economic%20boom.%20What%20comes%20next%20should%20worry%20every%20American%20business%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20reached%20the%20end%20of%20an%20era%20for%20the%20Chinese%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20three%20decades%2C%20China%20has%20been%20on%20the%20upswing%20of%20a%20supercycle%20that%20saw%20an%20almost%20uninterrupted%20expansion%20of%20the%20country's%20capacity%20to%20manufacture%2C%20appetite%20to%20consume%2C%20and%20ability%20to%20project%20power%20across%20the%20world%20economy.%20The%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20relentlessly%20pursued%20economic%20development%20over%20all%20else%2C%20even%20when%20that%20single-mindedness%20pushed%20the%20party%20to%20make%20debilitating%20policy%20mistakes%20%E2%80%94%20creating%20a%20massive%20bubble%20in%20the%20property%20market%2C%20sidling%20provinces%20with%20loads%20of%20debt%2C%20and%20failing%20to%20transition%20away%20from%20an%20overreliance%20on%20investment.%20There%20was%20no%20time%20to%20stop%20for%20corrections%20while%20China's%20mind%20was%20on%20money%20alone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20era%20of%20expansion%20was%20not%20only%20a%20boon%20for%20Beijing%2C%20it%20also%20helped%20fuel%20global%20demand.%20Countries%20relied%20on%20China's%20hunger%20for%20speedy%20modernization%20and%20industrial%20might%20to%20supercharge%20their%20own%20development.%20Even%20American%20companies%20saw%20China%20as%20the%20next%20great%20global%20market%20%E2%80%94%20and%20made%20bets%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20lost%20those%20bets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Xi%20Jinping%20has%20shifted%20the%20CCP's%20raison%20d'%C3%AAtre%20to%20national%20security%20over%20the%20economy.%20Getting%20rich%20isn't%20China's%20big%20project%20anymore%3B%20the%20project%20is%20power.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20both%20the%20government's%20priorities%20and%20behavior%20have%20changed.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20whenever%20it%20seemed%20like%20a%20recession%20was%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20the%20CCP%20came%20to%20rescue.%20There's%20no%20hefty%20stimulus%20coming%20this%20time.%20Nor%20will%20the%20explosive%20growth%20that%20experts%20once%20expected%20from%20China%20return.%20Beijing's%20relationship%20with%20the%20outside%20world%20is%20no%20longer%20guided%20by%20the%20principles%20of%20economic%20rationality%2C%20but%20rather%20its%20yearning%20for%20political%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20isn't%20about%20the%20economy%20anymore%2C%20it's%20all%20about%20advanced%20technology%20and%20weaponry%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20Miller%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20Chinese%20economic%20surveyor%20China%20Beige%20Book%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20American%20businesses%20need%20to%20consider%20how%20else%20Beijing's%20decision-making%20may%20now%20be%20flipped%20on%20its%20axis.%20For%20everyone%20from%20American%20farmers%20to%20pharmaceutical%20companies%2C%20this%20means%20shrinking%20demand%20and%20unstable%20supply%20chains.%20For%20policymakers%2C%20it%20means%20a%20China%20that%20is%20harder%20to%20mollify%20when%20conflicts%20arise.%20For%20the%20rest%20of%20us%2C%20it's%20a%20more%20precarious%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20spent%20economic%20system%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20economy%20has%20been%20bending%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20its%20structural%20problems%20for%20almost%20a%20decade%20now%2C%20but%20since%20the%20end%20of%20Xi's%20COVID-lockdown%20policy%2C%20it's%20become%20clear%20that%20its%20growth%20model%20is%20well%20and%20truly%20broken.%20Beijing's%20story%20so%20far%20has%20been%20to%20claim%20that%2C%20like%20other%20economies%20on%20the%20mend%20from%20the%20pandemic%2C%20China%20will%20in%20time%20resume%20its%20normal%20growth%20pattern.%20Instead%2C%20it%20looks%20like%20the%20economy%20is%20falling%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20start%20with%20the%20country's%20real-estate%20market%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20which%20cannot%20be%20overstated.%20Not%20only%20is%20it%20the%20biggest%20source%20of%20wealth%20for%20Chinese%20households%2C%20real%20estate%20is%20also%20the%20mechanism%20through%20which%20local%20governments%20are%20financed.%20Instead%20of%20property%20taxes%2C%20municipalities%20sell%20large%20swaths%20of%20land%20to%20property%20developers%20and%20then%20use%20the%20revenue%20for%20basic%20social%20services%20like%20fixing%20roads%20and%20paying%20out%20pensions.%20Cities%20like%20Shanghai%20and%20Beijing%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%2C%20but%20they%20make%20up%20just%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20property%20market.%20Property%20firms%20did%20the%20most%20building%20in%20third-tier%20cities%20where%20people%20aren't%20as%20wealthy.%20This%20is%20where%20you'll%20find%20China's%20infamous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-empty-homes-real-estate-evergrande-housing-market-problem-2021-10%5C%22%3Eghost%20cities.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20clear%20for%20years%20that%20the%20Chinese%20real-estate%20market%20has%20been%20in%20trouble.%20China%20has%20a%20population%20of%201.4%20billion%2C%20but%20it%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-vacant-homes-3-billion-people-housing-crisis-ex-official-2023-9%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20housing%20for%20a%20population%20of%203%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20expert%20estimates.%20Many%20of%20the%20mega-developments%20became%20empty%20monuments%20to%20Beijing's%20insatiable%20desire%20for%20growth.%20In%20Shenyang%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-ghost-town-deserted-chinese-mega-villas-overrun-farmers-2023-7%5C%22%3Efarmers%20have%20taken%20over%20a%20development%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20empty%20mansions%20for%20cattle%20grazing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorried%20that%20the%20sector%20would%20implode%2C%20Beijing%20attempted%20on%20multiple%20occasions%20to%20limit%20the%20credit%20that%20was%20fueling%20the%20bubble.%20But%20because%20real%20estate%20played%20such%20a%20vital%20role%20as%20a%20government-funding%20mechanism%2C%20China%20had%20to%20keep%20building%2C%20despite%20these%20troubles.%20Authorities%20didn't%20want%20to%20change%20the%20way%20local%20governments%20funded%20themselves%20or%20allow%20Chinese%20household%20finances%20to%20crumble%2C%20so%20they%20could%20not%20let%20prices%20fall.%20That%20credit%20addiction%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chinese%20real%20estate%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F649b2ded6eb0a800194d5ec2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Chinese%20real%20estate%20sector%20%E2%80%94%20built%20on%20government-fueled%20speculation%20and%20a%20massive%20amount%20of%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20is%20starting%20to%20break%20down.%3Cp%3EChina%20Photos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20system%2C%20supported%20by%20speculation%20and%20easy%20money%2C%20is%20starting%20to%20break%20down.%20Country%20Garden%2C%20China's%20largest%20real-estate%20developer%2C%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20collapse.%20In%20a%20sign%20that%20Beijing%20has%20grown%20tired%20of%20this%20game%2C%20Xu%20Jiayin%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20Evergrande%2C%20another%20embattled%20real-estate%20behemoth%2C%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fevergrande-founder-joins-list-chinese-tycoons-investigated-arrested-2023-09-29%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetained%20by%20%3C%2Fa%3Eauthorities.%20Money-starved%20provinces%20are%20being%20forced%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Feconomy%2Fchina-economy%2Farticle%2F3230828%2Fchina-debt-these-3-regions-have-most-daunting-debt-piles-so-what-can-be-done-about-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eask%20for%20bailouts%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20federal%20government%20doesn't%20want%20to%20give%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F20e82fb4-681d-4f41-934c-d64be061351c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esell%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20local%20governments%20claim%20are%20illiquid.%20The%20country's%20massive%2C%20opaque%20shadow-banking%20sector%2C%20which%20served%20as%20the%20backbone%20for%20the%20real-estate%20boom%2C%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchinas-shadow-banks-could-be-another-property-casualty-3ea302ed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20least%20one%20%2487%20billion%20money%20manager%2C%C2%A0%20Zhongrong%20Trust%2C%20skipped%20payments%20to%20investors%20this%20summer%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-08-17%2Fchina-police-visit-shadow-bank-investors-at-home-to-quash-unrest%3Fsref%3D6ZE6q2XR%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esparking%20protests%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20not%20been%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20so%20many%20developers%20are%20defaulting%20and%20consumers%20are%20questioning%20whether%20or%20not%20they%20should%20prepay%20for%20an%20apartment%2C%26quot%3B%20Charlene%20Chu%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20and%20senior%20analyst%20at%20Autonomous%20Research%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBefore%20they%20were%20thinking%2C%20'Prices%20are%20rising%20so%20fast%2C%20I%20need%20to%20get%20in.'%20Now%20prices%20are%20declining%20and%20the%20urgency%20to%20buy%20has%20vanished%2C%20so%20they're%20waiting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficial%20data%20has%20shown%20relatively%20modest%20price%20declines%20so%20far%2C%20but%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-hiding-bad-data-economy-debt-real-estate-2023-8%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20data%20coming%20from%20Biejing%20these%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20take%20those%20numbers%20seriously.%20Private%20data%20shows%20prices%20falling%20by%2015%25%20in%20metropolises%20like%20Shenzhen%20and%20Shanghai.%20In%20tier-two%20and%20tier-three%20cities%2C%20prices%20have%20fallen%20by%20as%20much%20as%2050%25%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2F2023-08-17%2Fchina-s-housing-slump-much-worse-than-official-data-show-video%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BEighty%20percent%20of%20all%20sales%20by%20area%20are%20in%20tier-three%20and%20below%20cities%2C%26quot%3B%20Chu%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20many%20of%20these%20places%20are%20facing%20long-term%20structural%20problems.%20%26quot%3BIf%20their%20market%20doesn't%20come%20back%2C%20the%20entire%20market%20doesn't%20come%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELittle%20fires%20everywhere%20all%20at%20once%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real-estate%20sector%20is%20the%20most%20visible%20sign%20of%20China's%20fading%20star%2C%20but%20other%20key%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%20are%20showing%20strain%20as%20well.%20While%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20is%20battling%20inflation%2C%20China%20is%20still%20in%20deflationary%20mode.%20August%20CPI%20came%20in%20at%200.1%25%2C%20up%20from%20minus-0.3%25%20the%20month%20before%2C%20showing%20an%20overall%20lack%20of%20domestic%20demand.%20Exports%20%E2%80%94%20which%20make%20up%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchinese-economys-export-pillar-shows-cracks-global-slowdown-2022-09-15%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DExports%2520are%2520vital%2520to%2520China%2Ceven%2520as%2520outbound%2520shipments%2520slow.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E40%25%20of%20the%20country's%20GDP%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20hit%20their%20lowest%20level%20in%20three%20years%20in%20July%2C%20falling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-trade-markets-exports-geopolitics-xi-beijing-russia-2023-8%3Fop%3D1%5C%22%3E14%25%20from%20the%20same%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20year%20before.%20August%20export%20figures%20showed%20some%20improvement%20but%20still%20came%20in%20down%208.8%25%20from%20the%20year%20before.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20Autonomous%20expects%20China's%20exports%20to%20slow%208%25%20compared%20to%20last%20year.%20Chu%20%E2%80%94%20who%20has%20been%20called%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB10001424127887323423804579025353329689102%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erock%20star%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20of%20Chinese%20debt%20analysis%20%E2%80%94%20told%20me%20that%20this%20weakness%20is%20not%20just%20a%20result%20of%20a%20cyclical%20downturn%3B%20it's%20a%20part%20of%20a%20more%20permanent%20shifting%20of%20supply%20chains%20caused%20by%20trade%20tensions%20with%20Europe%20and%20the%20US.%20These%20are%20powerful%20forces%20that%20are%20not%20easily%20reversed.%20Once%20multinational%20corporations%20no%20longer%20see%20China%20as%20a%20source%20of%20steady%20growth%2C%20they%20could%20begin%20changing%20their%20plans%20to%20invest.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20domestic%20anxiety%20about%20shrinking%20employment%20may%20change%20the%20basic%20consumer%20behavior%20that%20powered%20China's%20rise.%20This%20can%20create%20a%20vicious%2C%20self-reinforcing%20cycle%20that%20keeps%20investment%20out%20and%20spending%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20authorities%20are%20playing%20a%20game%20of%20whack-a-mole%2C%20trying%20to%20contain%20any%20shocks%20to%20the%20financial%20system%20because%20they%20fear%20social%20instability.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EChu%20started%20the%20year%20with%20one%20of%20the%20weakest%20growth%20outlooks%20for%20China%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20and%20the%20second%20half%20is%20looking%20worse.%20Autonomous'%20proprietary%20growth%20index%20for%20China%2C%20the%20Real%20Autono%20Economic%20Activity%20Composite%2C%20projects%20the%20country's%20economy%20to%20grow%20by%203.8%25%20for%20all%20of%202023%2C%20down%20from%20its%20original%204.2%25%20projection%20in%20January%20%E2%80%94%20and%20worse%20than%20Autonomous%20projected%20during%20the%20depths%20of%20China's%20COVID%20lockdown.%20Beijing%20is%20projecting%205%25%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20and%20given%20how%20tightly%20the%20CCP%20likes%20to%20manage%20expectations%2C%20officials%20will%20stick%20to%20that%20number%20come%20hell%20or%20high%20water.%20It's%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20double-digit%20growth%20policymakers%20used%20to%20demand%20and%20a%20signal%20to%20the%20Chinese%20people%20that%20Beijing%20is%20not%20going%20to%20direct%20its%20banks%20to%20spew%20credit%20to%20get%20the%20economy%20moving%20faster%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVictor%20Shih%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%2021st%20Century%20China%20Center%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%20San%20Diego%2C%20told%20me%20that%20when%20people%20ask%20him%20if%20there%20will%20be%20a%20financial%20crisis%20in%20China%2C%20he%20tells%20them%20that%20China%20%26quot%3Bis%20constantly%20in%20a%20financial%20crisis.%26quot%3B%20It's%20like%20the%20authorities%20are%20playing%20a%20game%20of%20whack-a-mole%2C%20trying%20to%20contain%20any%20shocks%20to%20the%20financial%20system%20because%20they%20fear%20social%20instability.%20That%20means%20there%20can%20be%20no%20correction%2C%20but%20if%20there's%20no%20correction%2C%20there's%20no%20deleveraging%2C%20and%20if%20there's%20no%20deleveraging%2C%20the%20moles%20will%20only%20multiply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EZombies%20in%20the%20Middle%20Kingdom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economy%20has%20put%20Beijing%20in%20a%20bind.%20There's%20too%20much%20for%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20to%20do%2C%20and%20not%20enough%20money%20or%20time%20to%20do%20it.%20Allowing%20a%20property-market%20correction%2C%20bailing%20out%20local%20governments%2C%20creating%20a%20new%20funding%20mechanism%20for%20them%2C%20developing%20a%20social%20safety%20net%20for%20the%20people%20through%20all%20this%20instability%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20it%20costs%20money.%20And%20even%20if%20the%20capital%20were%20there%2C%20policymakers%20fear%20what%20this%20disruption%20could%20do%20to%20their%20grip%20on%20power.%20Falling%20property%20prices%20and%20shrinking%20exports%20would%20weigh%20on%20the%20Chinese%20people's%20wealth%2C%20and%20the%20government%20is%20concerned%20that%20a%20meaningful%20correction%20would%20cause%20unrest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20there%20are%20severe%20property-price%20declines%2C%20Beijing%20views%20it%20as%20a%20risk%20to%20social%20stability%2C%26quot%3B%20Chu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20Beijing%20may%20need%20to%20conserve%20its%20firepower%20for%20other%20concerns%20coming%20down%20the%20pipeline.%20In%20the%20long-term%2C%20the%20CCP%20has%20to%20worry%20about%20China's%20demographics.%20Thanks%20to%20government%20mandates%20like%20the%20one-child%20policy%2C%20the%20country's%20population%20is%20rapidly%20aging%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20started%20to%20decline%20in%202022.%20The%20workforce%20will%20soon%20begin%20shrinking%3A%20Right%20now%20there%20are%20three%20working-age%20adults%20for%20every%20retired%20person%20in%20China%2C%20according%20to%20data%20compiled%20by%20J%20Capital%20Research%2C%20and%20by%202050%2C%20that%20ratio%20will%20hit%20one%20to%20one.%20Without%20booming%20property%20prices%20or%20continued%20growth%2C%20the%20growing%20pool%20of%20retirees%20will%20put%20a%20heavy%20burden%20on%20China's%20threadbare%20social%20safety%20net.%20GDP%20per%20capita%20is%20currently%20about%20%2412%2C800.%20When%20Japan%20started%20struggling%20in%201991%20with%20a%20similar%20dynamic%20%E2%80%94%20aging%20population%2C%20sky-high%20debt%2C%20and%20slowing%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20its%20GDP%20per%20capita%20was%20more%20than%20triple%20that%20amount%2C%20at%20%2441%2C266%20in%20today's%20dollars.%20China%20will%20get%20old%20before%20it%20gets%20rich%2C%20placing%20the%20task%20of%20growing%20the%20economy%20on%20fewer%20and%20fewer%20people%20as%20time%20goes%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EGetting%20rich%20isn't%20China's%20big%20project%20anymore%3B%20the%20project%20is%20power.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20really%20a%20shame%20is%20that%20China%20never%20seized%20the%20opportunity%20on%20the%20way%20up%20to%20build%20a%20comprehensive%20social%20safety%20net%20where%20people%20feel%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20for%20a%20rainy%20day%20%E2%80%94%20for%20healthcare%2C%20education%2C%20what%20have%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Chu%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BMost%20Chinese%20people%20do%20not%20feel%20they%20are%20covered%20for%20everything%20they%20need%20%E2%80%A6%20This%20is%20what's%20going%20to%20make%20moving%20to%20the%20domestic%2C%20demand-driven%20model%20difficult.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnless%20dramatic%20action%20is%20taken%2C%20the%20future%20of%20China's%20economy%20is%20looking%20less%20like%20a%20young%20dynamo%20and%20more%20like%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-hiding-bad-data-economy-debt-real-estate-2023-8%5C%22%3Eold%2C%20slow-moving%20blob%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20week%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported%20that%20policymakers%20are%20considering%20a%20modest%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Feconomy%2Fchina-weighs-new-stimulus-higher-deficit-to-meet-growth-target-18005381.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24137%20billion%20stimulus%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20just%20enough%20to%20meet%20its%20already%20comparatively%20low%20annual%20growth%20target%2C%20and%20nothing%20in%20the%20way%20of%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20healthy%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20it's%20just%20the%20zombie%20parts%20that%20have%20to%20be%20dealt%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20Shih%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20look%20like%20they%20are%20doing%20that%20now%2C%20but%20it%20will%20be%20a%20bigger%20and%20bigger%20drag%20on%20growth.%20I%20think%20the%20slow%20growth%20will%20cause%20such%20a%20serious%20employment%20and%20capital-flight%20problem%2C%20there%20could%20be%20political%20instability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20again%2C%20that's%20could%2C%20not%20%3Cem%3Ewill.%20%3C%2Fem%3EAnd%20because%20its%20priority%20is%20now%20power%20%E2%80%94%20where%20gains%20are%20much%20more%20idiosyncratic%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20risk%20that%20Beijing%20has%20shown%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20new%2C%20more%20dangerous%20era%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20Chinese%20policymakers%20connect%20political%20stability%20and%20economic%20growth%20is%20dogma%20in%20the%20West%2C%20but%20what%20we're%20witnessing%20now%20suggests%20that's%20not%20the%20case%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20not%20in%20practice.%20Beijing%20has%20not%20spent%20money%20on%20%E2%80%94%20or%20talked%20about%20raising%20money%20for%20%E2%80%94%20social%20programs%20for%20its%20aging%20population%2C%20nor%20has%20it%20made%20any%20attempts%20to%20tackle%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20for%20young%20families.%20If%20economic%20modernization%20was%20the%20most%20important%20thing%2C%20these%20would%20have%20been%20on%20the%20docket%20years%20ago.%20But%20they're%20not.%20Policymakers%20don't%20want%20an%20implosion%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20pushing%20for%20warp-speed%20development%20anymore%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20policies%20are%20now%20determined%20by%20Xi%20Jinping%20himself%2C%20and%20his%20priorities%20are%20spending%20money%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20technology%20and%20national-security%20race%20with%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20Shih%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22China's%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b08f5617692f0d03cc378%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Xi%20Jinping%20has%20shifted%20China's%20priorities%20from%20economic%20growth%20to%20what%20one%20experts%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Btechnology%20and%20national-security%20race%20with%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ELintao%20Zhang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20upon%20a%20time%2C%20infrastructure%20and%20property%20were%20the%20big%20beneficiaries%20of%20Beijing's%20largess%2C%20now%20it's%20the%20military.%20US%20government%20estimates%20put%20China's%20annual%20defense%20budget%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F09%2F19%2Fchina-defense-budget-military-weapons-purchasing-power%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earound%20%24700%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20much%20higher%20than%20independent%20NGO%20estimates%20of%20around%20%24290%20million%20and%20just%20shy%20of%20what%20the%20US%20spends%20on%20defense%20annually%2C%20%24800%20million.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20talking%20about%20the%20economic%20relationship%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20there%20just%20isn't%20that%20much%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20China%20Beige%20Book's%20Miller%20told%20me%20over%20the%20phone.%20%26quot%3BThe%20worry%20we%20have%20is%20not%20that%20Chinese%20consumers%20will%20do%20even%20less.%20It's%20that%20all%20the%20global%20supply%20chains%20are%20intermixed%20in%20industries%20like%20pharmaceutical%20and%20green%20tech.%20If%20things%20get%20too%20tense%2C%20it's%20potential%20supply-chain%20snarls%20that%20coil%20and%20screw%20up%20US%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20told%20me%20that%20multinational%20corporations%20are%20not%20only%20unsure%20of%20where%20to%20go%20next%2C%20they%20also%20lack%20full%20transparency%20as%20to%20where%20China%20impacts%20some%20supply%20chains.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20that%20we%20have%20a%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20that%20we%20don't%20even%20know%20how%20big%20the%20problem%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20never%20been%20a%20big%20consumer%20of%20American%20imports%2C%20but%20certain%20sectors%20will%20get%20hurt%20as%20our%20trade%20relationship%20is%20reset.%20A%20faltering%20Chinese%20economy%20will%20suppress%20demand%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-08-09%2Fchinese-deflation-another-worrying-signal-for-commodities-demand%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20commodities%20like%20oil%20seeds%20and%20grain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hitting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piie.com%2Fblogs%2Frealtime-economics%2Ffive-years-trade-war-china-continues-its-slow-decoupling-us-exports%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20farmers%20especially%20hard%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20will%20also%20eat%20into%20corporate%20profits%20for%20companies%20such%20as%20Nike%20and%20Starbucks%20that%20made%20large%20bets%20on%20Chinese%20consumers.%20US%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F05%2Ftechnology%2Fchip-makers-china-lobbying.html%3Fcampaign_id%3D4%26emc%3Dedit_dk_20231006%26instance_id%3D104562%