he%20government%20needs%20to%20figure%20out%20a%20way%20to%20help%20fund%20early%20childhood%20for%2C%20not%20just%20for%20teachers%20and%20businesses%2C%20but%20for%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Rescue%20Plan%20bill%20helped%20centers%20pay%20their%20employees%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20but%20as%20much%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproviders-struggle-to-keep-funding-rising-childcare-costs-2023-9%5C%22%3Epandemic-era%20funding%20ended%20at%20the%20end%20of%20September%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20childcare%20centers%20may%20soon%20be%20forced%20to%20close%20or%20make%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChildcare%20can%20be%20expensive%20and%20there's%20a%20'caregiver%20supply-chain%20crisis'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.dol.gov%2F2023%2F01%2F24%2Fnew-childcare-data-shows-prices-are-untenable-for-families%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Labor%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%20that%20putting%20a%20kid%20in%20childcare%20costs%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20year%2C%20in%20every%20part%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20her%20center%20had%20to%20increase%20its%20tuition%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20the%20annual%20cost%20for%20kids%20under%203%20who%20attended%20the%20CAST%20Preschool%20and%20Childcare%20Center%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20from%209%20a.m.%20to%2012%20p.m.%2C%20increased%20from%20%244%2C680%20for%20the%202019-2020%20school%20year%20to%20%245%2C263%20for%20the%202023-2024%20school%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20Robinson%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20talent%20marketplace%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthemomproject.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Mom%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20parents%20have%20to%20think%20about%20%26quot%3Bchildcare%20as%20an%20investment%20in%20your%20career%26quot%3B%20when%20weighing%20the%20expense%20of%20paying%20for%20care%20against%20the%20opportunity%20cost%20of%20stay-at-home%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobinson%20added%20that%20childcare%20accessibility%20is%20also%20a%20major%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20major%20kind%20of%20caregiver-supply-chain%20crisis%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Robinson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20childcare%20deserts%20where%20many%20families%20don't%20actually%20have%20access%20to%20quality%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20hard%20for%20centers%20to%20find%20staff%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20teachers%20had%20worked%20for%20CAST%20Preschool%20and%20Childcare%20Center%20for%20at%20least%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20a%20single%20mother%2C%20and%20because%20I%20knew%20childcare%20was%20really%20expensive%2C%20I%20started%20hiring%20young%20mothers%20and%20offered%20childcare%20for%20free%20for%20their%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Clark%20said%20she%20was%20usually%20fully%20staffed%2C%20she%20knew%20of%20many%20centers%20that%20had%20to%20close%20classrooms%20because%20they%20couldn't%20find%20enough%20teachers.%20Additionally%2C%20Clark%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20centers%20are%20being%20sold%20to%20corporations%20or%20other%20entities%20that%20have%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproviders-struggle-to-keep-funding-rising-childcare-costs-2023-9%5C%22%3Echildcare%20funding%20cliff%3C%2Fa%3E%20cuts%20off%20key%20support%20to%20providers%2C%20Julie%20Kashen%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20and%20the%20director%20for%20women's%20economic%20justice%20at%20The%20Century%20Foundation%2C%20told%20Insider%20two%20actions%20childcare%20centers%20may%20resort%20to%20so%20they%20can%20keep%20business%20running%20are%20increasing%20rates%20or%20closing%20a%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20more%20that%20centers%20close%20classrooms%20and%20the%20more%20they%20go%20out%20of%20business%2C%20it%20provides%20a%20real%20challenge%20for%20parents%20to%20find%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20finding%20infant%20and%20toddler%20care%20is%20particularly%20difficult.%20Centers%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20legally%20required%20ratio%20of%20teachers%20to%20kids.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20now%20have%20two%20nurseries%2C%20and%20we%20try%20to%20limit%20them%20to%20seven%20babies%20in%20each%20side%20because%20ratios%20are%20one-to-four%2C%20but%20seven%20babies%20for%20two%20people%20is%20still%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20your%20overhead%20and%20your%20labor%20costs%20are%20a%20lot%2C%20even%20though%20you're%20not%20really%20paying%20those%20people%20what%20they%20deserve%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20work%20is%20'a%20labor%20of%20love'%20that%20deserves%20good%20pay%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%20prices%20have%20put%20childcare%20out%20of%20the%20reach%20of%20many%20families%2C%20Clark%20said%20that%20that%20many%20providers%20still%20don't%20make%20%26quot%3Benough%20to%20run%20a%20childcare%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20put%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20into%20my%20teachers%2C%20as%20much%20as%20I%20could%2C%20and%20still%20I%20wasn't%20paying%20them%20what%20they're%20worth%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20noting%20this%20as%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20it%20was%20time%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20her%20workers%20made%20between%20%2415%20and%20%2420%20an%20hour%2C%20per%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEarly-childhood%20educators%20do%20not%20make%20what%20they're%20worth%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20it's%20more%20than%20a%20job.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20a%20passion%20because%20you%20don't%20do%20it%20for%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20described%20the%20job%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20labor%20of%20love%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added%20%26quot%3Bit%20should%20be%20a%20labor%20of%20love%20that%20pays%20well.%26quot%3B%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Foes%2Fcurrent%2Foes_nat.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics'%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20the%20median%20wage%20for%20childcare%20workers%20in%202022%20was%20%2413.71%20an%20hour%2C%20compared%20to%20%2422.26%20an%20hour%20for%20all%20occupations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20ended%20up%20selling%20to%20a%20business%20that%20could%20really%20afford%20to%20run%20the%20business%20the%20way%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20run%2C%20and%20hopefully%20we'll%20take%20care%20of%20the%20teachers%20the%20way%20they%20should%20be%20taken%20care%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20was%20also%20diagnosed%20with%20cancer%20in%202019%2C%20another%20reason%20she%20thought%20it%20was%20time%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20a%20cancer%20diagnosis%2C%20you%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20longer%20you%20have%20in%20your%20life%2C%20and%20I%20did%20want%20to%20spend%20some%20quality%20time%20with%20my%20husband%2C%20and%20there%20are%20things%20we%20want%20to%20do%20as%20a%20couple%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20was%20time%2C%20and%20also%20the%20pandemic%20was%20difficult%2C%20and%20you%20just%20don't%20know%20what's%20around%20the%20corner.%20So%20I%20did%20want%20to%20take%20some%20time%20for%20myself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20had%20to%20sell%20your%20business%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20family%20who%20has%20seen%20your%20childcare%20costs%20increase%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40insider.com%5C%