n.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpowerful-earthquake-shakes-west-afghanistan-a-week-after-devastating-quakes-hit-same-region%2Famp_articleshow%2F104442083.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpowerful-earthquake-shakes-west-afghanistan-a-week-after-devastating-quakes-hit-same-region%2Famp_articleshow%2F104442083.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Exploring%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20Forays%20Into%20Socialist%20Virtue%20Ethics%20and%20Minor%20Characters%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15150558%2Fimage-1390.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20protagonists%20without%20minor%20characters.%20It%E2%80%99s%20only%20against%20the%20shifting%20backdrop%20of%20minor%20characters%20that%20a%20protagonist%20attains%20prominent%20individuality.%20Too%20flat%20a%20treatment%20of%20minor%20characters%20risks%20flattening%20the%20protagonist%20as%20well%2C%20while%20too%20nuanced%20a%20portrait%20of%20minor%20characters%20takes%20up%20narrative%20space%20that%20the%20protagonist%20should%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlex%20Wolloch%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.princeton.edu%2Fbooks%2Fpaperback%2F9780691113142%2Fthe-one-vs-the-many%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20this%20ancient%20tension%20lets%20me%20characterise%20Chandan%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EAnother%20India%3A%20Events%2C%20Memories%2C%20People%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%20an%20exploration%20of%20the%20open%20set%20of%20minor%20characters%20that%20make%20up%20cultural%20identities%20in%20modern%20Karnataka%2C%20displacing%20the%20protagonist%20that%20is%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20361px)%2085vw%2C%20361px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15145654%2Fimage-1389-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22361%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15145654%2Fimage-1389-1.png%20455w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15145654%2Fimage-1389-1-213x300.png%20213w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680214%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22509%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChandan%20Gowda%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EAnother%20India%3A%20Events%2C%20Memories%2C%20People%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ESimon%20%26amp%3B%20Schuster%2C%20(September%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20book%20comprises%20essays%20that%20complement%20this%20open-endedness.%20True%20to%20the%20origins%20of%20the%20genre%20among%20early%20modern%20Europeans%20whose%20encounters%20with%20the%20New%20World%20led%20Montaigne%20to%20realise%20how%20European%20identities%20were%20only%20as%20accidental%20and%20provincial%20as%20those%20of%20the%20foreigners%20they%20encountered%2C%20these%20essays%20are%20tentative%20in%20spirit%2C%20openly%20dependent%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20personal%20encounters%20with%20books%2C%20authors%2C%20actors%2C%20farmers%2C%20and%20films%2C%20and%20free%20of%20the%20dogmatic%20closure%20of%20any%20one%20ideological%20commitment.%20As%20with%20Montaigne%2C%20the%20profundity%20of%20some%20of%20their%20arguments%20never%20compromises%20the%20clarity%20of%20their%20prose.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20without%20a%20stereotype%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20opening%20essay%2C%20reflecting%20on%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20national%20stereotype%20about%20a%20cultural%20identity%20for%20Karnataka.%20It%20reads%20this%20ambivalently%20as%20summoning%20%E2%80%9Cunease%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20failure%E2%80%9D%2C%20conveying%20a%20lack%20of%20power%20for%20those%20who%20wish%20to%20mark%20their%20presence%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20repertoire%20of%20sub-regional%20languages%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20also%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20delicious%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20book%20exploits%20this%20freedom%20to%20foreground%20what%20are%20mostly%20Kannada-language%20writers%2C%20film%20directors%2C%20actors%2C%20and%20even%20barbers%20as%20minor%20characters%20whose%20complexity%20has%20enabled%20a%20protagonist%20we%20glimpse%20in%20the%20background%3A%20an%20Indian%20federation%20owing%20its%20cultural%20pluralism%20to%20regional%20traditions%20of%20non-atheist%20socialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20then%2C%20is%20the%20ethical%20stake%20that%20implicitly%20or%20explicitly%20threads%20the%20essays%20together%3A%20a%20commitment%20to%20taking%20religion%20seriously%20as%20a%20site%20of%20collective%20moral%20imagination%2C%20of%20inter-generationally%20produced%20images%20of%20virtue%20that%2C%20on%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%20intellectuals%2C%20saints%20and%20artists%20Gowda%20focuses%20on%2C%20may%20orient%20and%20nuance%20distributive%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%20to%20the%20Marxist%20Sanskritist%20D.D.%20Kosambi%20(1907-66)%2C%20who%20tried%20to%20shoehorn%20the%20Carvakas%2C%20ancient%20Indian%20materialist%20philosophers%2C%20into%20his%20conception%20of%20them%20as%20proto-Marxist%20materialists%2C%20the%20villagers%2C%20artists%2C%20and%20authors%20in%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20essays%20effortlessly%20come%20across%20as%20indigenous%20socialists%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20they%20claim%20this%20label.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20selective%20conspectus%20of%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20themes%20should%20bring%20out%20its%20thematic%20variety%20and%20argumentative%20richness%3A%20we%20read%20of%20the%20recent%20waning%20of%20%E2%80%9Canimals%20as%20moral%20actors%E2%80%9D%20in%20Hindi%2C%20Tamil%2C%20and%20Kannada%20cinema%2C%20%E2%80%9Can%20impoverishment%20of%20worldview%3B%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Kannada%20film%20star%20Rajkumar%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20custodian%20of%20Kannada%20morality%E2%80%9D%20who%20%E2%80%9Cmoves%20smoothly%20across%20both%20modernity%20and%20tradition%E2%80%9D%20in%20his%20films%20set%20in%20the%20present%3B%20of%20how%20the%20great%20Kannada%20poet%20Kuvempu%E2%80%99s%20humanist%20critique%20of%20community%20identities%20as%20limiting%20led%20him%20to%20propose%20a%20new%20model%20of%20lost-cost%20marriage%20that%20crossed%20caste%20and%20religious%20lines%2C%20avoiding%20dowry%2C%20bride-price%20and%20horoscopes%3B%20of%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20women%20Sufi%20saints%20and%20their%20dargahs%20that%20are%20open%20to%20all%3B%20of%20the%2019th%20century%20Kannadiga%20Sufi%20Shishunala%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20trans-communitarian%20piety%3B%20the%20debate%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20Kannada%20press%20over%20Kuvempu%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20exclusion%20of%20Madhvacharya%2C%20the%2013th%20century%20dualist%20Vedantin%20philosopher%20from%20Karnataka%2C%20from%20his%20hymn%20to%20Karnataka%20because%20Madhvacharya%20deemed%20Shudras%20and%20women%20unworthy%20or%20incapable%20of%20spiritual%20liberation%3B%20of%20the%20folklorist%20and%20Dalit%20leader%20Siddalingaiah%E2%80%99s%20initial%20disapproval%20of%20and%20eventual%20affection%20for%20the%20eccentric%20intimacy%20between%20villagers%20and%20their%20village%20deities%3B%20of%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%E2%80%99s%20innovative%20socialist%20ideal%20of%20a%20non-violent%20and%20multi-part%20%E2%80%9Ctotal%20revolution%3B%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20trans-communitarian%20lyricism%20of%20the%20Kannada%20poet%20Nissar%20Ahmed%3B%20of%20the%20farmer%20Narayana%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20successful%20adoption%20of%20the%20Japanese%20natural%20farmer%20Fukuoka%E2%80%99s%20methods%20from%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EOne%20Straw%20Revolution%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20resume%20my%20opening%20metaphor%2C%20Karnataka%20thus%20comes%20across%20as%20a%20large%20realist%20novel%20made%20up%20wholly%20of%20morally%20particular%20minor%20characters%2C%20ranging%20in%20their%20moods%20from%20scholarly%20sobriety%20to%20folkloric%20hilarity%20and%20lyricism%3B%20and%20commanding%20genres%20that%20include%20political%20theory%2C%20poetry%2C%20folklore%2C%20theatre%2C%20journalism%2C%20cinema%2C%20and%20farming%20philosophy.%20That%20this%20cast%20of%20minor%20characters%20includes%20North%20Indian%20socialists%20like%20J.P.%20Narayan%20and%20Ram%20Manohar%20Lohia%20signals%20the%20openness%20to%20socialism%20that%20has%20distinguished%20the%20history%20of%20the%20old%20Mysore%20State%20from%20the%20Marxism%20that%20was%20prominent%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20the%20Ambedkarism%20prominent%20in%20Maharashtra.%20But%20Gail%20Omvedt%20who%20made%20this%20observation%20in%201994%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FDalits-Democratic-Revolution-Ambedkar-Movement%2Fdp%2F0803991401%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CLohiaism%2C%20then%2C%20did%20not%20come%20to%20Karnataka%20as%20an%20ideology%20of%20full-scale%20Dalit%20liberation%20but%20rather%20as%20a%20reformist%20trend%20which%20was%20in%20some%20ways%20compatible%20with%20the%20liberal%20co-optation%20patterns%20that%20had%20been%20established%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ERam-raj%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20atmosphere%20of%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOmvedt%20might%20have%20critiqued%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20book%20by%20arguing%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20stereotyped%20Karnataka%20identity%20and%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20openness%20to%20plural%20moral-religious%20visions%20are%20mutually%20complementary%20aspects%20of%20the%20same%20assimilationist%20and%20reformist%20rather%20than%20radical%20political%20culture.%20But%20let%20me%20conclude%20by%20proposing%20another%20frame%20of%20reference.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPhilosophical%20discussion%20of%20ethics%20has%20distinguished%20between%20deontology%2C%20consequentialism%2C%20and%20virtue%20ethics.%20Whereas%20deontological%20ethics%20prescribes%20rules%20for%20moral%20behaviour%20and%20consequentialism%20assesses%20actions%20by%20their%20moral%20consequences%2C%20virtue%20ethics%20concerns%20itself%20with%20moral%20states%20of%20being%20as%20ends%20in%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGowda%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20a%20contribution%20to%20virtue%20ethics%20and%2C%20as%20such%2C%20an%20implicit%20response%20to%20Alasdair%20MacIntyre%E2%80%99s%20(1981)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FAfter-Virtue-Study-Moral-Theory%2Fdp%2F0268035040%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAfter%20Virtue%3A%20A%20Study%20in%20Moral%20Theory%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20MacIntyre%20argues%20that%20the%20abandonment%20of%20Aristotelian%20ethics%20during%20the%20European%20Enlightenment%20was%20the%20abandonment%20of%20teleological%20ethics%2C%20of%20a%20collective%20consensus%20on%20where%20and%20how%20we%20want%20to%20end%20up%20by%20the%20practice%20of%20virtue.%20He%20opposed%20the%20individualist%20or%20subjective%20ethics%20that%20arose%20in%20its%20place%20by%20calling%20for%20a%20return%20to%20Aristotle%E2%80%99s%20model%20of%20community%20ethics%20oriented%20towards%20collective%20happiness.%20The%20many%20overlapping%20moral%20visions%20in%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20essays%20present%20small-scale%20and%20internally%20heterogeneous%20socialism%20as%20a%20collective%20ethical%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20essays%E2%80%99%20explorations%20of%20virtue%20ethics%20are%20distinguished%20by%20their%20recognition%20that%20virtue%20is%20more%20effectively%20taught%20and%20learned%20by%20stories%20about%20human%20individuals%20than%20by%20prescription%20(deontological%20ethics)%20or%20means-end%20reasoning%20(consequentialist%20ethics).%20Hence%2C%20the%20salience%20of%20personalities%20in%20these%20essays%3A%20Raj%20Kumar%2C%20Puneeth%20Rajkumar%2C%20Kuvempu%2C%20Siddalingiah%2C%20Elah%20Bhatt%2C%20Sara%20Aboobacker%2C%20and%20others.%20Each%20embodies%20her%20or%20his%20virtues%20because%20of%20their%20narrative%20frames%3A%20the%20films%20they%20act%20in%2C%20the%20novels%20or%20stories%20or%20plays%20they%20write%20and%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20own%20anecdotes%20about%20them.%20Virtue%20ethics%20that%20depend%20on%20narrative%20for%20its%20illocutionary%20force%20also%20depends%20on%20people%20who%20recognise%20its%20language%20(here%20Kannada%2C%20English%2C%20Hindi)%20and%20poetic%20conventions%20(here%20vacanas%2C%20a%20Sanskrit%20encyclopedia%2C%20folklore%2C%20theatre%2C%20Puranas%2C%20cinema%E2%80%A6)%20%E2%80%93%20in%20other%20words%2C%20an%20interpretive%20community.%20Karnataka%20is%20here%20an%20open%20set%20of%20interpretive%20communities%2C%20each%20purveyed%20to%20us%20by%20its%20morally%20eccentric%20minor%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20value%20of%20this%20emphasis%20on%20narrative%20modes%20for%20virtue%20ethics%20is%20that%20it%20avoids%20oppressive%2C%20top-down%2C%20state-led%20projects%20that%20characterise%20deontological%20ethics%20(Plato%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ERepublic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EManusm%E1%B9%9Biti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EShar%E2%80%98ia%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20leaving%20emulation%20up%20to%20the%20reader%20or%20listener%20and%20keeping%20space%20open%20for%20small-scale%20experimentation%2C%20relativism%20and%20humane%20openness%20to%20error.%20Whence%20the%20importance%20of%20humour%20to%20the%20Dalit%20intellectuals%20Siddalingiah%20and%20D.R.%20Nagaraj%20and%20to%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20essays%20on%20them%2C%20humour%20that%20expresses%2C%20not%20the%20failure%20of%20reformist%20projects%2C%20but%20the%20impossibility%20of%20such%20an%20all-encompassing%20ethical%20project%20in%20the%20first%20place%3B%20and%20the%20necessity%20for%20ethical%20pluralism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20as%20elsewhere%2C%20the%20political%20ascendancy%20of%20fascist%20nationalism%20has%20been%20catastrophic%20for%20everyday%20ethics.%20This%20book%20offers%20reprieve%20to%20those%20of%20us%20not%20hypnotised%20by%20spectacles%20of%20nationalism%2C%20letting%20us%20turn%20from%20its%20glare%20towards%20the%20gentler%20lights%20of%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20many%20small-scale%20forays%20into%20socialist%20virtue%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrashant%20Keshavmurthy%20is%20associate%20professor%20of%20Persian-Iranian%20Studies%20at%20the%20Institute%20of%20Islamic%20Studies%2C%20McGill%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn1%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexploring-karnatakas-forays-into-socialist-virtue-ethics-and-minor-characters%23_ftnref1%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697364312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15150558%2Fimage-1390.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexploring-karnatakas-forays-into-socialist-virtue-ethics-and-minor-characters%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chandan%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20'Another%20India%3A%20Events%2C%20Memories%2C%20People'%C2%A0is%20an%20exploration%20of%20the%20open%20set%20of%20minor%20characters%20that%20make%20up%20cultural%20identities%20in%20modern%20Karnataka%2C%20displacing%20the%20protagonist%20that%20is%20India.%20This%20book%20comprises%20essays%20that%20complement%20this%20open-endedness.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexploring-karnatakas-forays-into-socialist-virtue-ethics-and-minor-characters%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CIA%20intel%20about%20looming%20Hamas%20attacks%20did%20not%20reach%20Joe%20Biden%20%E2%80%94%20dismissed%20as%20routine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224889%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rocket%20barrages%20launched%20towards%20Israel%20from%20Gaza.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652141c76e038039826ca483%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERocket%20barrages%20launched%20towards%20Israel%20from%20Gaza.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20CIA%20issued%20two%20reports%20warning%20the%20Biden%20administration%20of%20increased%20Hamas%20threats%20days%20before%20attacks.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ENeither%20Joe%20Biden%20nor%20other%20senior%20White%20House%20officials%20were%20briefed%20on%20the%20reports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EEgypt%20and%20Israel%20also%20had%20intelligence%20suggesting%20an%20upcoming%20onslaught.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fantoniopequenoiv%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fcia-issued-warnings-about-potential-escalated-hamas-attacks-on-israel-days-before-strike%2F%3Fsh%3D71dec18a5186%5C%22%3ECIA%20issued%20warnings%20about%20a%20potential%20escalation%20of%20Hamas%20attacks%20on%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%20days%20ahead%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-declares-state-of-war-hamas-launches-massive-surprise-attack-2023-10%5C%22%3EOperation%20Al-Aqsa%20Flood%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20say%20reports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20reports%20warned%20of%20the%20looming%20coordinated%20attacks%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fcia-reports-gaza-hamas-israel.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20first%2C%20dated%20September%2028%2C%20indicated%20a%20heightened%20risk%20of%20violence%20and%20the%20possibility%20of%20rocket%20strikes%20by%20Hamas%20into%20Israel%20spanning%20multiple%20days.%20The%20second%20report%2C%20dated%20October%205%2C%20issued%20two%20days%20before%20Hamas%20carried%20out%20its%20attack%2C%20warned%20of%20an%20increased%20probability%20of%20violence%20from%20the%20militant%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fpolitics%2Fus-intelligence-warnings-potential-gaza-clash-days-before-attack%5C%22%3Ewarnings%20did%20not%20reach%20the%20desk%20of%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20or%20senior%20White%20House%20officials%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20CNN.%20The%20CIA%20did%20not%20consider%20the%20reports%20to%20have%20particular%20significance%20to%20policymakers.%20It%20has%20raised%20concerns%