%20Muslims%20from%20bidding%20for%20stalls%20even%20in%20public%20spaces%20near%20the%20temples%20ahead%20of%20religious%20festivals%20in%20summer%20last%20year%20and%20later%20during%20Dasara.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Mangaladevi%20Temple%E2%80%99s%20management%20recently%20decided%20not%20to%20allot%20stalls%20to%20Muslim%20traders%20even%20on%20the%20street%20opposite%20the%20shrine.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20never%20faced%20such%20a%20ban%20until%20last%20year%20when%20some%20Hindu%20organisations%20objected%20to%20Muslim%20vendors%20setting%20up%20temporary%20stalls%20at%20temple%20fairs%2C%E2%80%9D%20committee%20convener%20B.K.%20Imthiyaz%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20we%20are%20now%20seeking%20permission%20(from%20district%20authorities%20in%20Dakshina%20Kannada%20and%20Udupi)%20to%20conduct%20our%20business%2C%20which%20is%20our%20livelihood.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImthiyaz%20underscored%20that%20Muslims%20were%20not%20seeking%20permission%20to%20run%20stalls%20inside%20temple%20premises.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20we%20are%20asking%20is%20for%20permission%20to%20open%20stalls%20on%20public%20roads%20that%20come%20under%20the%20city%20civic%20body%20and%20not%20the%20temples%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ban%20on%20Muslim%20vendors%20participating%20in%20temple%20fairs%20in%20Karnataka%20started%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20hijab%20controversy%20in%20the%20state%2C%20which%20was%20under%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHindu%20organisations%20framed%20the%20ban%20as%20a%20response%20to%20the%20shutdown%20enforced%20by%20Muslim%20groups%20in%20protest%20against%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkarnataka-high-court-order-hijab-ban-constitutional-principles%5C%22%3EKarnataka%20high%20court%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20upheld%20the%20ban%20on%20wearing%20hijabs%20in%20schools%20and%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20government%20at%20the%20time%20used%20the%20Hindu%20Religious%20Institutions%20and%20Charitable%20Endowments%20Rules%2C%20established%20in%202002%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.firstpost.com%2Findia%2Fban-on-muslim-traders-in-karnataka-temples-citing-2002-rule-understanding-what-the-law-actually-says-10501301.html%5C%22%3Eto%20justify%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20prohibition%2C%20arguing%20that%20non-Hindus%20were%20not%20permitted%20to%20engage%20in%20any%20business%20within%20temple%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20traders%E2%80%99%20association%2C%20representing%20various%20communities%2C%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20significant%20losses%20suffered%20by%20Muslim%20vendors%20due%20to%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20bans%20on%20their%20participation%20in%20temple%20fairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Dakshina%20Kannada%20district%2C%20about%20half%20of%20the%20vendors%20were%20Muslim%2C%20according%20to%C2%A0%20Imthiyaz.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20body%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20the%20interests%20of%20Muslims.%20Our%20president%20is%20Jain%2C%20and%20there%20are%20Hindus%20and%20Christians%20among%20us%20who%20are%20seeking%20equal%20rights%20in%20the%20bidding%20process%20for%20stalls%20at%20temple%20fairs%20and%20festivals%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697351766000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F29142337%2FScreenshot-2023-01-29-at-2.23.32-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkarnataka-traders-body-urges-to-lift-ban-on-muslim-vendors-in-temple-fairs-for-dasara-festival%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Last%20year%2C%20many%20shrines%20had%20banned%20Muslim%20vendors%20from%20these%20fairs%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20Sangh%20parivar%20groups.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkarnataka-traders-body-urges-to-lift-ban-on-muslim-vendors-in-templ