%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Need%20to%20Activate%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20New%20Aerial%20Gateways%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15103202%2Fimage-1384.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20ahead%20of%20his%20visit%20to%20Kathmandu%20in%202019%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Chinese%20people%20especially%20want%20to%20visit%20Nepal.%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20extolled%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20beauty%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DRPxSS9K_MkM%5C%22%3Espeaking%20before%20parliament%20in%202014%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20incapacity%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20government%20and%20private%20operators%20is%20that%20we%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20cash%20in%20on%20the%20disclosures%20and%20admiration%20of%20President%20Xi%20or%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%20to%20use%20as%20marketing%20tools%20to%20fly%20in%20high-end%20tourists%20from%20all%20over%20China%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20we%20do%20in%20Nepal%20is%20bemoan%20our%20fate%20that%20the%20hotels%20are%20empty%2C%20or%20that%20neither%20Pokhara%20and%20Bhairawa%20airports%20have%20international%20flights.%20The%20air%20bridges%20are%20rusting%20with%20lack%20of%20use%20at%20the%20%24215%20million%20Pokhara%20airport%2C%20and%20foreign%20airlines%20have%20not%20shown%20an%20interest%20in%20using%20Bhairawa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20blame%20is%20mostly%20placed%20on%20New%20Delhi%20which%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20has%20made%20things%20difficult%20for%20Nepali%20aviation.%20Inbound%20international%20flights%20have%20to%20be%20routed%20through%20the%20Simara%20waypoint%2C%20while%20only%20outbound%20flights%20can%20use%20Mahendranagar%20or%20Janakpur.%20New%20Delhi%20has%20also%20not%20allowed%20inbound%20flights%20to%20descend%20through%20Indian%20air%20space%20to%20Bhairawa%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHimalayan%20Airlines%2C%20which%20has%20Chinese%20investment%20and%20more%20jets%20than%20Nepal%20Airlines%2C%20is%20barred%20from%20serving%20Indian%20cities.%20At%20Kathmandu%20airport%20passengers%20boarding%20Indian-owned%20airlines%20have%20to%20pass%20through%20cabooses%20attached%20to%20the%20ramps%20to%20be%20frisked%20by%20Indian%20security%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20Nepalis%20do%20complain%20too%20much%20while%20doing%20very%20little%20to%20find%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20be%20sure%20that%20Sher%20Bahadur%20Deuba%20and%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20have%20not%20made%20a%20strong%20and%20continuous%20case%20on%20the%20air%20corridors%20that%20Nepal%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20existing%20opportunities%20that%20do%20not%20have%20to%20involve%20India%20at%20all.%20Bhairawa%20airport%20is%20the%20gateway%20to%20the%20Lumbini-Kapilvastu%20Buddhist%20circuit%2C%20and%20we%20should%20be%20drawing%20in%20pilgrims%20directly%20from%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20Korea%2C%20Thailand%2C%20Burma%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Singapore%20and%20Sri%20Lanka.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20countries%20are%20located%20to%20the%20east%20of%20Nepal%2C%20which%20means%20not%20getting%20descent%20clearance%20over%20Indian%20air%20space%20into%20Bhairawa%20is%20immaterial%20since%20all%20flights%20from%20Lhasa%2FChengdu%20or%20Bangkok%2FYangon%20would%20track%20to%20Simara%20anyway%20before%20approaching%20the%20airport%20from%20the%20east.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFlights%20to%20Pokhara%20or%20Bhairawa%20descending%20from%20the%20West%20would%20just%20have%20to%20take%20an%20extra%20dozen%20minutes%20to%20route%20via%20Simara%2C%20which%20seems%20a%20handicap%20that%20could%20be%20managed.%20Departures%20are%20no%20problem%20from%20both%20airports%20since%20airway%20L626%20towards%20Dhangadi%20is%20open%20for%20outbound%20flights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPokhara%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20exotic%20destinations%20in%20Asia%2C%20with%20its%20proximity%20to%20Annapurna%2C%20lakes%2C%20trekking%2C%20adventure%20sports%2C%20and%20ornithological%20wonders.%20It%20is%20also%20the%20staging%20point%20for%20Muktinath%2C%20Mustang%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnepalitimes.com%2Fbanner%2Fthe-abcs-of-a-winter-trek-in-nepal%5C%22%3EAnnapurna%20Circuit%2FSanctuary%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20city%20became%20popular%20with%20Chinese%20travellers%20pre-COVID%20after%20a%20Chinese%20TV%20serial%20called%20it%20%E2%80%98a%20place%20to%20visit%20before%20one%20dies%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPokhara%20is%20right%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20Nepal%2C%20whereas%20Kathmandu%20is%20towards%20the%20east.%20If%20there%20are%20flights%2C%20many%20migrant%20workers%20who%20make%20up%20more%20than%20half%20the%20outbound%20passengers%20from%20Kathmandu%20could%20choose%20to%20fly%20out%20of%20Pokhara.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20cannot%20simply%20build%20hotel%20rooms%20and%20hope%20the%20tourists%20will%20come.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20both%20Pokhara%20and%20Bhairawa%2C%20the%20lethargy%20of%20the%20government%20is%20complemented%20by%20the%20lack%20of%20marketing%20imagination%20of%20the%20private%20sector.%20Pokhara%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20the%20hotel-bed%20capacity%20to%20host%20a%20dozen%20international%20flights%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20new%20dimensions%20and%20challenges%20to%20tourism%20today%20that%20need%20to%20be%20addressed.%20Regional%20air%20pollution%20is%20obscuring%20the%20views%20of%20the%20Himalaya%2C%20which%20is%20adversely%20impacting%20tourists.%20Given%20that%20tourism%20contributes%20up%20to%2010%25%20of%20global%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20there%20is%20eco-guilt%20and%20flight%20shaming%20which%20are%20discouraging%20tourists%20from%20long-distance%20travel%2C%20particularly%20from%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20much%20to%20be%20done%20to%20get%20Beijing%20to%20open%20up%20the%20China-Nepal%20land%20borders%20for%20tourism.%20The%20Humla%20route%20into%20Manasarovar%20needs%20to%20be%20preserved%2C%20and%20the%20exotic%20faraway%20view%20of%20Manasarovar-Kailash%20from%20Limi%20in%20Humla%20needs%20promotion%20and%20the%20route%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETourists%20will%20not%20flood%20through%20Bhairawa%20just%20because%20it%20serves%20Lumbini.%20Most%20pilgrims%20want%20to%20do%20the%20entire%20circuit%20including%20Kushinagar%2C%20Bodhgaya%20and%20Sarnath%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPresently%2C%20most%20international%20Buddhist%20pilgrims%20make%20a%20quick%20half-day%20trip%20from%20India%20to%20Nepal%20even%20though%20they%20do%20not%20have%20a%20Nepal%20visa.%20Mostly%2C%20they%20bring%20lunch%20packets%20and%20make%20a%20quick%20turnaround.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20Bhairawa%20airport%20viable%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20politicians%20need%20to%20sit%20down%20for%20some%20hard%20talk%20with%20their%20counterparts%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20They%20need%20to%20make%20the%20argument%20that%20if%20overseas%20pilgrims%20can%20come%20across%20Nepal%2C%20they%20should%20have%20access%20to%20the%20Indian%20side%20as%20well.%20Granted%20that%20there%20are%20more%20places%20to%20visit%20in%20India%2C%20but%20a%20border%20is%20a%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20tour%20operators%20alert%20pilgrims%20that%20they%20should%20also%20get%20Indian%20visas%2C%20they%20can%20arrive%20in%20Nepal%20through%20Kathmandu%2C%20Pokhara%20or%20Bhairawa%2C%20also%20tour%20Indian%20holy%20sites%2C%20return%20to%20Nepal%20and%20fly%20out.%20This%20is%20not%20impossible%20to%20do%2C%20it%20just%20needs%20some%20commitment%20to%20tourism%20and%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20some%20imagination.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnepalitimes.com%2Fhere-now%2Factivating-the-new-aerial-gateways%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnepalitimes.com%2F%5C%22%3ENepali%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697346189000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in