20warned%20a%20cross-section%20of%20service%20veterans%20and%20military%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Stockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute%20(SIPRI)%2C%20India%20had%20imported%2045%25%20of%20its%20defence%20equipment%20from%20Russia%20between%202018-22%2C%20and%20while%20no%20analogous%20data%20was%20available%20for%20Israeli%20materiel%20buys%2C%20analysts%20estimated%20that%20Tel%20Aviv%20had%20provided%20around%209-10%25%20of%20the%20varied%20military%20kits%20New%20Delhi%20received%20during%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20equalled%20a%20whopping%2055%25%20or%20so%20of%20Russian%20and%20Israeli%20military%20imports%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20SIPRI%20recently%20revealed%20that%2037%25%20of%20all%20Israeli%20arms%20exports%20between%202018-22%20were%20to%20India%2C%20registering%20a%20175%25%20increase%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Hindu%20nationalist%20Bhartiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)-led%20government%20assumed%20power%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERetired%20Brigadier%20Rahul%20Bhonsle%20of%20the%20Security%20Risks%20Asia%20consultancy%20in%20Delhi%20said%20that%20while%20the%20BJP-led%20government%20had%20launched%20the%20%3Cem%3Eatamnirbhar%3C%2Fem%3E%20initiative%20to%20indigenise%20Indian%20military%20needs%2C%20Delhi%20still%20topped%20the%20global%20list%20of%20defence%20equipment%20importers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20in%20light%20of%20the%20ongoing%20conflicts%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20now%20in%20Gaza%2C%20Russia%20and%20Israel%2C%20he%20warned%2C%20could%20well%20end%20up%20either%20failing%20to%20meet%20India%E2%80%99s%20numerous%20materiel%20requirements%20or%20delaying%20deliveries%20interminably.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Russia%2C%20Israel%20does%20not%20provide%20India%20any%20major%20platforms%2C%20but%20supplies%20critical%20and%20innovative%20force%20multipliers%20like%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles%20(UAV)%2C%20assorted%20missile%2C%20guidance%20and%20avionics%20systems%2C%20precision-guided%20munitions%2C%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3Ediverse%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Esensors%20and%20surveillance%20and%20targeting%20radars%2C%20amongst%20other%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20this%20was%20fitted%20onto%20combat%20aircraft%2C%20helicopters%2C%20warships%2C%20submarines%20and%20armoured%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20such%20equipment%20and%20component%20diversity%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20quantify%20the%20exact%20or%20even%20near-%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3Eprecise%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Epercentages%20of%20Israeli%20military%20equipment%20in%20service%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20armed%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECollaborative%20Indo-Israeli%20ventures%20to%20locally%20develop%20and%20manufacture%20missile%20systems%2C%20UAVs%20and%20small%20arms%20too%20rendered%20such%20an%20audit%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3Echallenging%2C%20resulting%20in%20approximations.%20Inordinately%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Ehigh%20levels%20of%20secrecy%20surrounding%20all%20India-Israel%20military%20and%20security-related%20commerce%20further%20added%20to%20the%20overall%20opacity%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frooting-for-israel-not-a-good-word-about-palestine-modi-is-upending-indian-foreign-policy%5C%22%3ERooting%20for%20Israel%2C%20Not%20a%20Good%20Word%20About%20Palestine%3A%20Modi%20Is%20Upending%20Indian%20Foreign%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20though%20recent%20local%20media%20reports%2C%20quoting%20defence%20officials%2C%20stated%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Gaza%20against%20Hamas%20was%20%E2%80%98unlikely%E2%80%99%20to%20impact%20military%20hardware%20and%20spares%20supplies%20to%20India%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20they%20cautioned%20that%20an%20extended%20conflict%20could%20jeopardise%20deliveries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20limited%20impact%20%5Bon%20Israeli%20equipment%20supplies%5D%20can%20only%20be%20%5Badversely%5D%20felt%20if%20it%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20a%20long-drawn%20war%2C%20much%20like%20the%20one%20between%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fmilitary-supplies-from-israel-unlikely-to-be-affected-govt-8982029%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20Saturday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20quoting%20an%20unnamed%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20an%20eventuality%2C%20Israel%20may%20end%20up%20diverting%20its%20weapons%20and%20equipment%20stock%20towards%20fighting%20its%20own%20conflict%2C%20the%20official%20had%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%20Delhi%20established%20formal%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Tel%20Aviv%20in%201992%2C%20Israel%20had%20assisted%20India%20clandestinely%20in%201962%20by%20providing%20it%20limited%20military%20aid%20during%20its%20brief%2C%20albeit%20disastrous%20war%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20Chief%20of%20Staff%2C%20General%20David%20Shaltiel%2C%20had%20visited%20Delhi%20surreptitiously%20soon%20after%20in%201963%2C%20and%20thereafter%20Israel%20provided%20similar%2C%20albeit%20paltry%20assistance%20during%20India%E2%80%99s%20subsequent%20wars%20with%20Pakistan%20in%201965%20and%201971%20by%20supplying%20munitions%20like%20Finnish-origin%20M-58%20160mm%20mortars.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClandestine%20ties%20continued%20apace%2C%20with%20senior%20Indian%20security%20officials%20travelling%20to%20Israel%20via%20Cyprus%20%E2%80%93%20as%20no%20direct%20air%20links%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20existed%20%E2%80%93%20to%20ensure%20that%20their%20passports%20would%20have%20no%20record%20of%20their%20visit%20to%20the%20Jewish%20state%20out%20of%20sympathy%20for%20and%20support%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20assassination%20in%201984%2C%20India%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20secured%20Israeli%20help%20in%20upgrading%20its%20VIP%20protection%20protocol%20by%20training%20and%20arming%20its%20newly%20raised%20Special%20Protection%20Group%20and%20National%20Security%20Guard%20personnel.%20Israeli%20specialists%20also%20seemingly%20devised%20Prime%20Minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20security%20architecture%20that%20broadly%20continues%20with%20minor%20alterations%20for%20his%20successors%2C%20including%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q-1024x683.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q-1024x683.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680092%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThousands%20of%20Israelis%20and%20Palestinians%20have%20died%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40UNRWA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20disintegration%20in%20the%20early%201990s%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20longstanding%20ally%20and%20principal%20weapons%20supplier%2C%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20military%20ties%20with%20Israel.%20Crucial%20supplies%20of%20arms%20and%20spares%20for%20military%20equipment%20either%20ceased%20or%20were%20interminably%20delayed%2C%20as%20overnight%20numerous%20suppliers%20found%20themselves%20located%20in%20independent%20neighbouring%20republics%20that%20were%20inimical%20to%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20India%20was%20compelled%20to%20consider%20alternate%20materiel%20sources%20at%20a%20critical%20period%20that%20coincided%20with%20the%20eruption%20of%20Kashmiri%20insurgency%20in%20late%201989%2C%20in%20response%20to%20which%20the%20army%20was%20widely%20deployed%20in%20the%20troubled%20Himalayan%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Israel%20were%20instituted%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narasimha%20Rao%20in%201992%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20fast-tracked%20their%20strategic%20and%20defence%20relationship%20based%20on%20mutual%20security%20and%20commercial%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20rightly%20perceived%20a%20commercial%20opportunity%2C%20while%20India%20looked%20upon%20Tel%20Aviv%20as%20a%20reliable%20and%20%E2%80%98no-questions-asked%E2%80%99%20materiel%20provider%2C%20especially%20of%20varied%20ammunition%20and%20missile%20systems%20which%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%20badly%20lacked%2C%20and%20still%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20it%20still%20took%20another%20six-odd%20years%20and%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20ascent%20to%20power%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Behari%20Vajpayee%20for%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20defence%20machinery%20to%20definitively%20establish%20itself%20in%20India.%20Being%20a%20%E2%80%98closet%E2%80%99%20nuclear%20weapon%20state%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20decision%20not%20to%20condemn%20India%E2%80%99s%20May%201998%20Pokhran%20nuclear%20tests%20also%20helped%20considerably%2C%20further%20endearing%20Tel%20Aviv%20to%20Delhi%20and%20vice-versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20was%20the%2011-week%20long%20Kargil%20war%20with%20Pakistan%20in%201999%20that%20catapulted%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20defence%20industry%20to%20centre%20stage%20domestically.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20seriousness%20of%20the%20deadly%20conflict%20unfolded%2C%20commercially%20savvy%20Israel%20dug%20deep%20into%20its%20military%20reserves%20to%20supply%20India%20high-end%20hardware%2C%20especially%20badly-needed%20155mm%20rounds%20for%20its%20FH-77B%20Bofors%20howitzers%2C%20laser-guided%20munitions%20and%20other%20ordnance%20that%20contributed%20largely%20to%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20vacating%20the%20mountainous%20region%E2%80%99s%20siege%20and%20ending%20hostilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Without%20Israel's%20Oppression%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20Hamas%20Terrorism%20Would%20Have%20Never%20Existed%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwithout-israels-oppression-of-palestinians-hamas-terrorism-would-have-never-existed%5C%22%3EWithout%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Oppression%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20Hamas%20Terrorism%20Would%20Have%20Never%20Existed%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3ETwo%20decades%20later%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%E2%80%99s%20(IAF%E2%80%99s)%20Mirage%202000H%20fighters%20in%20their%20attack%20on%20a%20Pakistani%20militant%20training%20camp%20at%20Balakot%20in%20Pakhtunkhwa%20in%20February%202019%2C%20fired%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3Especifically%20configured%20Israeli%20Crystal%20Maze%20Mk2%20missiles%20(variants%20of%20the%20Rafael%20Advanced%20Defence%20Systems%20AGM-142%20Raptor%20Have%20Nap%2FPopeye%20missile).%20Additionally%2C%20they%20employed%C2%A0Paveway%20II%C2%A0laser-guided%20bombs%20directed%20by%20Rafael-designed%C2%A0Smart%C2%A0Precise%20Impact%20and%20Cost%20Effective%20(SPICE)%20guidance%20kits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlongside%2C%20the%20Indian%20military%20exhibited%20interest%20in%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%E2%80%99%20successful%20warfare%20strategies%20and%20concepts%2C%20particularly%20with%20regard%20to%20countering%20armed%20insurgencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIntelligence%20sharing%20on%20terrorism%20issues%20proliferated%2C%20as%20did%20Israeli%20military%20training%20assistance%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20Special%20Forces.%20The%20rationale%20that%20Israel%20and%20India%20shared%20similar%2C%20but%20un-publicised%20concerns%20over%20threats%20posed%20by%20contiguous%20Islamic%20states%20further%20cemented%20bilateral%20security%20and%20military%20ties%20between%20Delhi%20and%20Tel%20Aviv.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20in%202008%2C%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20successfully%20placed%20an%20Israel%20Aerospace%20Industries%20(IAI)-designed%20TecSAR%20military%20satellite%20into%20polar%20orbit%20in%20a%20classified%20operation%20that%20appreciably%20augmented%20Tel%20Aviv%E2%80%99s%20intelligence-gathering%20capabilities%20by%20providing%2024-hour%20high-resolution%20imagery%20in%20all-weather%20conditions%20at%20an%20affordable%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20later%20followed%20up%20with%20the%20launch%20of%20RISAT-2%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20radar%20imaging%20satellite%20fitted%20with%20an%20IAI-provided%20X-band%20synthetic%20aperture%20radar%20(SAR)%2C%20to%20monitor%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20disputed%20border%20with%20Pakistan%20as%20part%20of%20its%20wider%20anti-terrorist%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20is%20also%20believed%20to%20have%20provided%20India%20with%20counter-terrorism%20assistance%20to%20help%20it%20deal%20with%20the%20Kashmiri%20insurgency%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20It%20made%20available%20over%20a%20dozen%20technical%20teams%20to%20assist%20India%20in%20augmenting%20its%20border%20intelligence%20gathering%20capabilities%2C%20besides%20providing%20anti-terrorism%20counter%20measures%20like%20upgraded%20border%20fencing%2C%20ground%20sensors%20and%20handheld%20thermal%20imagers%20for%20use%20by%20army%20and%20paramilitary%20border%20guards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fbopc9EQOEps%3Fsi%3D59pi6Ilnr44MaCvL%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20some%20of%20this%20type%20of%20fencing%20equipment%20deployed%20along%20the%20restive%20Israel-Gaza%20border%20had%20miserably%20failed%20in%20detecting%20last%20week%E2%80%99s%20Hamas%20assault%20on%20Israel%2C%20in%20which%20some%201%2C200%20Israelis%20died%20and%20which%20spawning%20the%20current%20hostilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20part%20of%20proliferating%20covert%20security%20and%20defence%20co-operation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-57887300%5C%22%3EIsrael%20had%20reportedly%20transferred%20military-grade%20Pegasus%20spyware%20to%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20deployed%20it%20to%20monitor%20smartphones%20belonging%20to%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20opposition%20politicians%2C%20journalists%2C%20lawyers%20and%20civil%20rights%20activists%20amongst%20others%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EModi%20was%20also%20the%20first%20Indian%20PM%20to%20visit%20Israel%20in%202017%2C%20while%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20travelled%20to%20Delhi%20in%20early%202018%20further%20cementing%20strategic%2C%20political%20and%20diplomatic%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20much%20has%20been%20detailed%20over%20the%20past%2020%20months%2C%20after%20Russia%20declared%20war%20on%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%2C%20on%20challenges%20the%20Indian%20military%20faces%20with%20regard%20to%20sourcing%20sundry%20military%20platforms%20and%20spares%20from%20Moscow%20due%20to%20the%20sanctions%20imposed%20upon%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20still%20awaits%20the%20delivery%20of%20two%20of%20five%20Almaz-Antey%20S-400%20Triumf%20self-propelled%20surface-to-air%20(SAM)%20missile%20systems%2C%20four%20Admiral%20Grigorovich%20Project%201135.6M%20frigates%20and%2075%2C000-80%2C0000%20Kalashnikov%20AK-203%207.62x39mm%20assault%20rifles%20that%20were%20part%20of%20a%20deal%20signed%20in%20late%202021%20to%20locally%20licence%20and%20build%20601%2C427%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fate%20of%20leasing%20one%20more%20Project%20971%20%E2%80%98Akula%E2%80%99%20(Schuka-B)-class%20nuclear%20powered%20submarine%20(SSN)%20by%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20(IN)%20too%20is%20unknown%20for%20now.%20Additionally%2C%20spares%20and%20sub-assemblies%20for%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20large%20fleet%20of%20Russian%20Su-30MKIs%2C%20MiG-29Ms%20and%20MiG-21s%20too%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20in%20short%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3EOver%2065%25%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3Eof%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%E2%80%99s%20assets%20are%20of%20Soviet%20and%20Russian%20origin%2C%20necessitating%20the%20continued%20servicing%2C%20maintenance%2C%20overhaul%20and%20in%20some%20instances%20upgradation%20of%20a%20large%20proportion%20of%20them%20by%20their%20original%20equipment%20manufacturers%20or%20OEMs%2C%20all%20of%20which%20had%20been%20sanctioned%20by%20the%20US%2C%20its%20NATO%20allies%2C%20Australia%20and%20Japan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20though%20India%20had%20reduced%20its%20dependence%20on%20Russia%20for%20military%20equipment%20by%20some%2033%25%20between%202011%20and%202020%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20diversify%20its%20network%20of%20materiel%20suppliers%2C%20switching%20entirely%20to%20alternate%20sources%20was%20not%20an%20option%20military-planners%20in%20Delhi%20desired%2C%20as%20it%20entailed%20colossal%20expenditure%2C%20reworked%20infrastructure%2C%20inordinate%20delays%20and%20doctrinal%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN-US%5C%22%3Eindividual%3C%2Fspan%3E%20wars%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%20and%20the%20constraints%20these%20could%20impose%20on%20Russia%20and%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20export%20defence%20equipment%20may%20end%20up%20providing%20alternative%20routes%20to%20sustain%20and%20modernise%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%20through%20indigenous%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697297495000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14174919%2FUkraine-and-Gaza.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fukraine-gaza-materiel-exports-to-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%2065%25%C2%A0of%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%E2%80%99s%20assets%20are%20of%20Soviet%20and%20Russian%20origin%2C%20and%20India%20and%20Israel%20also%20have%20a%20history%20of%20collaborating%20on%20strategic%20and%20defence%20matters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fukraine-gaza-materiel-exports-to-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22British%20parents%20'trapped'%20at%20Gaza-Egypt%20border%20'like%20caged%20hens%20waiting%20to%20die'%2C%20says%20son%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697297220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-gaza-israel-raffa-crossing_6321578.jpg%3F20231014195443%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-foreign-nationals-gather-at-rafah-crossing-gaza-egypt-border-ahead-of-limited-reopening-12984410%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20British-Palestinian%20dual%20nationals%20who%20are%20waiting%20at%20Gaza's%20border%20with%20Egypt%20are%20%26quot%3Blike%20caged%20hens%20waiting%20to%20die%26quot%3B%2C%20their%20son%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-foreign-nationals-gather-at-rafah-crossing-gaza-egypt-border-ahead-of-limited-reopening-12984410%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-foreign-nationals-gather-at-rafah-crossing-gaza-egypt-border-ahead-of-limited-reopening-12984410%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-foreign-nationals-gather-at-rafah-crossing-gaza-egypt-border-ahead-of-limited-reopening-12984410%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20Read%20Haruki%20Murakami%20in%20English%20the%20%E2%80%98Japanese%20Way%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20In%20Four%20Steps%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14203453%2FHaruki.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20than%2040%20years%20of%20writing%20to%20choose%20from%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20difficult%20to%20know%20where%20to%20begin%20when%20reading%C2%A0Haruki%20Murakami.%20Earlier%20this%20year%20in%20Japan%2C%20he%20published%20his%2015th%20novel%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fap-tokyo-fukushima-madeleine-albright-hillary-clinton-b2318758.html%5C%22%3EThe%20City%20and%20Its%20Uncertain%20Walls%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20though%20the%20release%20date%20for%20an%20English%20translation%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Murakami%20first%20gained%20attention%20in%20the%20English-reading%20world%20with%20the%20translation%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wind-up%20Bird%20Chronicle%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201997%2C%20his%20writing%20career%20began%20almost%20two%20decades%20earlier%20with%20the%20publication%20of%20%3Cem%3EHear%20The%20Wind%20Sing%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EPinball%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20first%20two%20novels%20were%20not%20widely%20available%20in%20English%20until%202015%2C%20and%20consequently%2C%20Japanese%20and%20English%20readers%20have%20read%20Murakami%20in%20quite%20different%20contexts%20and%20chronologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20wrote%20his%20first%20works%2C%20the%20bristling%20Japanese%20bubble%20economy%20had%20not%20yet%20burst%20and%20the%20iron%20curtain%20still%20divided%20Europe.%20Whereas%20when%20he%20took%20English%20readers%20by%20storm%20in%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20days%20as%20the%20leading%20economic%20superpower%20were%20long%20gone%2C%20as%20was%20the%20tension%20of%20the%20cold%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20a%20four-step%20guide%20for%20English%20readers%20who%20wish%20to%20read%20Murakami%20in%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Japanese%20way%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20%3Cem%3ENorwegian%20Wood%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1987)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20work%20you%20should%20read%20is%20Murakami%E2%80%99s%20breakthrough%20novel%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.harukimurakami.com%2Fbook%2Fnorwegian-wood%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENorwegian%20Wood%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Although%20its%20immediate%20commercial%20success%20meant%20that%20it%20was%20published%20in%20English%20only%20two%20years%20later%2C%20the%20initial%20translation%20was%20intended%20for%20English%20language%20learners%20and%20was%20only%20available%20in%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20English%20version%20available%20across%20the%20world%20today%20is%20a%20re-translation%20from%202000.%20While%20this%20novel%20introduces%20the%20typical%20lonesome%2C%20first-person%20male%20narrator%20that%20is%20recognisable%20across%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20works%2C%20%3Cem%3ENorwegian%20Wood%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20in%20many%20ways%20not%20classic%20Murakami.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20takes%20place%20in%20a%20more%20realistic%20setting%20than%20those%20he%20later%20became%20known%20for.%20Still%2C%20I%20recommend%20starting%20with%20this%20novel%20because%20this%20is%20what%20most%20Japanese%20readers%20would%20have%20done%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERead%20it%20and%20think%20of%20how%20the%20world%20was%20back%20then.%20Why%20was%20a%20novel%20that%20introduces%20so%20much%20death%2C%20loss%20and%20regret%20embraced%20by%20Japanese%20readers%20right%20at%20a%20time%20when%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20surface%20at%20least%20%E2%80%93%20things%20could%20not%20have%20been%20better%20in%20their%20country%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14201335%2FJapan-1024x700.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14201335%2FJapan-1024x700.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14201335%2FJapan-300x205.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14201335%2FJapan.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680146%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22574%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFollowing%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20Japan%20experienced%20rapid%20and%20sustained%20economic%20growth%2C%20lasting%20till%20around%201991.%20Photo%3A%20%E4%B8%AD%E6%B0%8F%E3%81%AB%E3%82%88%E3%82%8B%E6%92%AE%E5%BD%B1%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Elephant%20Vanishes%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1993)%20%26amp%3B%20%3Cem%3EBlind%20Willow%20Sleeping%20Woman%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2006)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20you%20should%20read%20some%20of%20Murakami%E2%80%99s%20short%20stories.%20While%20most%20famous%20for%20his%20long%20novels%2C%20he%20has%20also%20written%20an%20impressive%20number%20of%20short%20stories%20%E2%80%93%20most%20of%20which%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20translated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Japan%2C%20short%20stories%20are%20usually%20first%20published%20ad%20hoc%20in%20literary%20magazines%20before%20being%20published%20in%20books.%20They%20are%20therefore%20rarely%20planned%20as%20full%20collections.%20The%20works%20included%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Elephant%20Vanishes%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EBlind%20Willow%20Sleeping%20Woman%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20selected%20from%20across%20his%20many%20short%20stories%2C%20specifically%20for%20English%20translation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20showcase%20stories%20from%20Murakami%E2%80%99s%20early%20and%20mid-career%2C%20and%20give%20an%20excellent%20overview%20of%20his%20diverse%20writing%20style.%20Note%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20few%20works%20with%20female%20and%20third-person%20narrators%2C%20a%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20male%20voice%20known%20so%20well%20to%20his%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wind-up%20Bird%20Chronicle%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1994)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20novel%20that%20put%20Murakami%20on%20the%20literary%20map%20in%20the%20English-reading%20world.%20The%20narrator%20is%20classic%20Murakami%20%E2%80%93%20a%20male%20protagonist%20in%20search%20of%20something%2C%20in%20this%20case%20first%20his%20cat%20and%20then%20his%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlong%20the%20way%2C%20he%20encounters%20inexplicable%20events%2C%20journeys%20to%20other%20worlds%2C%20and%20meets%20strange%20people.%20You%20may%20notice%20that%20some%20of%20the%20short%20stories%20from%20the%20two%20aforementioned%20collections%20work%20as%20forerunners%20for%20this%20novel.%20This%20clear%20connection%20between%20short%20stories%20and%20novels%20is%20typical%20of%20Murakami.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%2C%20or%20in%20tandem%20with%2C%20reading%20the%20novel%2C%20I%20recommend%20you%20read%20%3Cem%3ECreta%20Kano%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1990).%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20rather%20bizarre%20and%20ultra-short%20story%20which%20was%C2%A0only%20translated%20last%20year.%20Ask%20yourself%3A%20who%20is%20Creta%20Kano%3F%20And%20what%20is%20the%20implication%20for%20the%20novel%20that%20Japanese%20readers%20were%20able%20to%20read%20this%20short%20story%20first%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20%3Cem%3EHard-boiled%20Wonderland%20and%20the%20End%20of%20the%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1985)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20await%20the%20English%20translation%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20City%20and%20Its%20Uncertain%20Walls%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20you%20can%20prepare%20by%20looking%20at%20the%20closely%20related%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EHard-boiled%20Wonderland%20and%20the%20End%20of%20The%20World%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20language%20has%20several%20words%20for%20the%20pronoun%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20these%20two%20novels%20are%20told%20by%20two%20narrators%20using%20different%20versions%3A%20%3Cem%3Ewatashi%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eboku%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWithout%20alternative%20options%20for%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%9D%2C%20English%20translators%20of%20such%20stories%20are%20challenged.%20As%20a%20solution%2C%20chapters%20narrated%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3Ewatashi%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0character%20(a%20kind%20of%20cyberpunk%2C%20science%20fiction%20world)%20are%20written%20in%20the%20past%20tense%2C%20whereas%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eboku%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0character%E2%80%99s%20chapters%20(a%20more%20surreal%2C%20virtual%20fantasy%20world)%20are%20written%20in%20the%20present%20tense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThink%20of%20what%20this%20means%20in%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20general%20dreamlike%20setting%2C%20and%20look%20forward%20to%20discovering%20how%20this%20issue%20is%20addressed%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20City%20and%20Its%20Uncertain%20Walls%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGitte%20Marianne%20Hansen%2C%20Reader%20in%20Japanese%20Studies%2C%20Newcastle%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhow-to-read-haruki-murakami-in-english-the-japanese-way-in-four-steps-214918%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697296251000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14203453%2FHaruki.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Ffour-step-guide-